1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,882
The two bright-eyed stars loved by Gen MZ,

2
00:00:15,949 --> 00:00:18,718
we're here with Yu-jin and Park Jin-young.

3
00:00:18,785 --> 00:00:20,086
Jin-young has risen

4
00:00:20,153 --> 00:00:23,423
to an actor who has made
a presence for himself.

5
00:00:23,490 --> 00:00:26,826
-He's been starring in <i>Still Shining</i>…
-<i>Still Shining.</i>

6
00:00:26,893 --> 00:00:28,428
…and giving an excellent performance.

7
00:00:28,495 --> 00:00:30,163
Will you tell us about the series?

8
00:00:30,230 --> 00:00:31,398
-Sure.
-Okay.

9
00:00:31,464 --> 00:00:34,801
<i>Still Shining</i> is
about someone's first love.

10
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:36,803
THE FIRST LOVE OF ONE'S TEENAGE YEARS

11
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:38,038
<i>For some reason, we break up.</i>

12
00:00:38,104 --> 00:00:39,406
AFTER THE BREAKUP…

13
00:00:39,472 --> 00:00:42,275
<i>But then, in a decade, we reunite</i>

14
00:00:42,342 --> 00:00:45,378
<i>and fall back in love,</i>
<i>so it's a romance series.</i>

15
00:00:45,445 --> 00:00:48,948
We must share something
we're very grateful for.

16
00:00:49,015 --> 00:00:52,218
The production crew of <i>Still Shining</i> sent

17
00:00:52,285 --> 00:00:55,188
-<i>a coffee and snack truck to our shoot.</i>
-<i>Thank you.</i>

18
00:00:55,755 --> 00:00:56,956
THANK YOU

19
00:00:57,023 --> 00:00:58,525
-It's never happened before.
-I know.

20
00:00:58,591 --> 00:01:01,661
-It means the crew adores him that much.
-They must.

21
00:01:01,728 --> 00:01:03,663
Our set had a great vibe.

22
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:05,965
It was similar to this one,

23
00:01:06,032 --> 00:01:08,368
everyone joking around
and teasing each other,

24
00:01:08,435 --> 00:01:10,737
having a blast while laughing.

25
00:01:10,804 --> 00:01:12,405
After we're done,

26
00:01:12,472 --> 00:01:14,507
we don't even look at each other
and go right home.

27
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:15,942
-Is that so?
-It is.

28
00:01:16,009 --> 00:01:17,210
We're beaten in the greenroom.

29
00:01:18,945 --> 00:01:20,947
<i>They're like,</i>
<i>"Hey, you were funny back there."</i>

30
00:01:21,548 --> 00:01:24,184
THE SHOCKING TRUTH
BEHIND CHEF & MY FRIDGE

31
00:01:24,250 --> 00:01:26,152
Why would anyone beat you up
for being funny?

32
00:01:26,219 --> 00:01:29,923
-My chin almost got dislocated.
-"Get beaten"?

33
00:01:29,989 --> 00:01:31,658
But I hear our production crew

34
00:01:31,724 --> 00:01:35,428
-has lots of bones to pick with us.
-Our crew? For this show? Why?

35
00:01:35,495 --> 00:01:37,397
We got this coffee truck today,

36
00:01:37,464 --> 00:01:38,965
but Ho-young, Nam-no, and Sung-jun

37
00:01:39,666 --> 00:01:40,700
cleared it out.

38
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,335
-They destroyed it.
-Cut it out.

39
00:01:42,402 --> 00:01:45,338
Was that why I didn't see them
back in the greenroom?

40
00:01:45,405 --> 00:01:47,941
So the three boars went there
and raided the truck?

41
00:01:48,007 --> 00:01:49,075
WHOA!

42
00:01:49,142 --> 00:01:50,410
It's all mine!

43
00:01:50,477 --> 00:01:52,846
We should've built a stronger fence.

44
00:01:52,912 --> 00:01:54,581
HAHAHAHAHA

45
00:01:54,647 --> 00:01:56,082
They broke out.

46
00:01:56,149 --> 00:01:57,784
WHAT'S THAT SOUND?

47
00:01:57,851 --> 00:02:00,386
Our production crew
should've enjoyed the food.

48
00:02:00,453 --> 00:02:01,754
I just had some soup.

49
00:02:01,821 --> 00:02:03,523
The crew should've enjoyed the food.

50
00:02:03,590 --> 00:02:05,058
I just had a taste.

51
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:07,360
I was told to dig in, so I did.

52
00:02:08,061 --> 00:02:09,896
Then you should've finished eating there.

53
00:02:09,963 --> 00:02:12,432
You brought piles of food back.

54
00:02:12,499 --> 00:02:13,867
-Like at a buffet?
-Like how people

55
00:02:13,933 --> 00:02:15,602
bring back food in a plastic bag.

56
00:02:15,668 --> 00:02:17,103
The fish-shaped buns were good.

57
00:02:17,170 --> 00:02:18,638
What's that on your shirt?

58
00:02:18,705 --> 00:02:20,140
When I went to the food truck…

59
00:02:20,206 --> 00:02:22,041
It wasn't a food truck. Those were snacks.

60
00:02:22,509 --> 00:02:24,844
BOTH COVERING THEIR MOUTHS

61
00:02:24,911 --> 00:02:26,746
-It was a snack truck.
-I practically had a meal.

62
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:29,315
-He ate like it was a food truck!
-A food truck.

63
00:02:29,382 --> 00:02:30,383
You had a meal?

64
00:02:30,450 --> 00:02:32,418
There were stickers available,
so I put one here.

65
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:34,454
I'm such a huge fan of Jin-young's.

66
00:02:34,721 --> 00:02:36,055
THANK YOU

67
00:02:36,122 --> 00:02:37,590
Is he older than you?

68
00:02:37,657 --> 00:02:38,992
He's a year older than me.

69
00:02:39,058 --> 00:02:40,627
He was born in 1995. I knew that.

70
00:02:40,693 --> 00:02:42,428
You seem at least 40 years old.

71
00:02:42,795 --> 00:02:43,830
I'M STILL 32…

72
00:02:43,897 --> 00:02:44,931
Forty? Where'd that come from?

73
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:47,267
We can say Chef Sung-jun
has been over-fermented.

74
00:02:47,734 --> 00:02:49,002
PFFT

75
00:02:49,068 --> 00:02:51,704
It happens
when something is overly fermented

76
00:02:51,771 --> 00:02:53,873
-and turns wrinkly.
-Yu-jin is laughing too much.

77
00:02:53,940 --> 00:02:55,241
-He's over-fermented.
-Wait.

78
00:02:55,308 --> 00:02:57,544
Are we allowed to take it this far?

79
00:02:57,610 --> 00:02:59,212
This is a place

80
00:02:59,279 --> 00:03:01,681
where everyone is rude to one another
with every breath.

81
00:03:02,649 --> 00:03:04,884
-It's funny.
-He says we're rude with every breath.

82
00:03:04,951 --> 00:03:08,021
WHO LET OUT THAT RUDE BREATH?

83
00:03:08,087 --> 00:03:11,558
-Every time you speak… Really?
-Today is a friendly day.

84
00:03:11,624 --> 00:03:13,793
You should see them come after me.

85
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:15,662
Aren't your parents as old as Hyun-suk?

86
00:03:15,728 --> 00:03:17,163
He's the same age as my mom.

87
00:03:18,431 --> 00:03:21,834
-Little Tiger's mother was born in 1972.
-What?

88
00:03:21,901 --> 00:03:24,204
-Little Tiger?
-She was born in 1972?

89
00:03:24,270 --> 00:03:26,539
My mom was born in 1972 too.

90
00:03:26,806 --> 00:03:28,041
OH, THE TIME…

91
00:03:28,374 --> 00:03:30,210
STAY STRONG, DAD

92
00:03:30,643 --> 00:03:32,378
YOU GOT US HERE WITH YOU

93
00:03:32,445 --> 00:03:34,847
I'll wait and see
who leaves this world first.

94
00:03:35,148 --> 00:03:36,449
LEAVE WHERE?

95
00:03:36,516 --> 00:03:38,918
People come to life in order,
but we don't leave in order.

96
00:03:38,985 --> 00:03:40,253
I think he'll live long.

97
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,387
I'll hold out.

98
00:03:41,454 --> 00:03:44,691
IVE is known as the most popular group
among elementary school children.

99
00:03:44,757 --> 00:03:48,094
These days, some of our chefs
have become popular among them too.

100
00:03:48,161 --> 00:03:50,830
We received a letter
from an elementary school student,

101
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:53,566
and it was for Chef Hyun-suk.

102
00:03:53,633 --> 00:03:54,767
Let me read it for you.

103
00:03:54,834 --> 00:03:56,736
"Dear Chef Hyun-suk,

104
00:03:56,803 --> 00:03:59,572
I like you very, very much.

105
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:00,974
Chef Hyun-suk,

106
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,508
please do not become a grandpa.

107
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:06,079
I don't want you to go to heaven soon."

108
00:04:08,414 --> 00:04:10,049
Poong doesn't want it, either!

109
00:04:10,116 --> 00:04:11,818
A SILENT PRAYER

110
00:04:11,884 --> 00:04:13,453
Grandpa.

111
00:04:13,519 --> 00:04:17,490
<i>This letter was from Lee Ryu-ho.</i>

112
00:04:17,557 --> 00:04:19,659
-How sweet.
-Don't go to heaven too soon.

113
00:04:20,293 --> 00:04:21,628
That's so nice.

114
00:04:21,694 --> 00:04:23,463
It sounds like it's from a genuine fan,

115
00:04:23,529 --> 00:04:24,897
so I find it quite endearing.

116
00:04:24,964 --> 00:04:28,067
But on the other hand,
even grade school kids are attacking me.

117
00:04:28,134 --> 00:04:29,969
RYU-HO, YOU TOO?

118
00:04:30,036 --> 00:04:31,904
-He shows respect for the elderly.
-Yes.

119
00:04:31,971 --> 00:04:33,773
PISSED
RESPECT FOR THE ELDERLY?

120
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:36,342
He's wishing you longevity.

121
00:04:36,409 --> 00:04:39,646
-Yes.
-He doesn't want you to leave soon.

122
00:04:39,712 --> 00:04:41,848
Say something to him.

123
00:04:41,914 --> 00:04:44,384
Thank you for the letter, Ryu-ho.

124
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:46,219
I'll keep looking after my health

125
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:48,087
and leave for heaven much later.

126
00:04:48,388 --> 00:04:49,756
DON'T WORRY

127
00:04:49,822 --> 00:04:51,190
HAHAHAHAHA

128
00:04:51,257 --> 00:04:52,692
He just feels that close to you.

129
00:04:52,759 --> 00:04:54,894
-He sees you as a friend.
-Yes, like a friend.

130
00:04:54,961 --> 00:04:59,098
He keeps getting surprised
by Chef Nam-no's laughter.

131
00:04:59,165 --> 00:05:00,433
I can tell how close you all are.

132
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:02,101
When someone got teased,

133
00:05:02,168 --> 00:05:04,337
he laughed
as if he were mocking a close friend.

134
00:05:04,404 --> 00:05:05,571
It seemed like that.

135
00:05:05,638 --> 00:05:06,806
The bar is set to mockery.

136
00:05:06,873 --> 00:05:09,175
-That was a big laugh.
-Yes.

137
00:05:09,242 --> 00:05:11,411
The thing is, Jin-young debuted

138
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:14,013
-with JYP Entertainment.
-I did.

139
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:15,748
You have the same name as the CEO.

140
00:05:15,815 --> 00:05:18,184
-That's right.
-He's Park Jin-young too.

141
00:05:18,251 --> 00:05:19,952
Do you have any stories to tell?

142
00:05:20,019 --> 00:05:22,522
You'll see later
when you go through my fridge

143
00:05:22,588 --> 00:05:24,891
that my mom often sends me kimchi.

144
00:05:24,957 --> 00:05:27,293
One day, the parcel had arrived,
but I couldn't find it.

145
00:05:27,860 --> 00:05:29,262
I GET IT!

146
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:31,597
It turned out that
he had taken one of my parcels.

147
00:05:31,664 --> 00:05:32,865
DELIVERY MISHAP

148
00:05:32,932 --> 00:05:34,534
-That could happen.
-Oh, my.

149
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:36,769
Have you ever taken his parcels?

150
00:05:37,437 --> 00:05:39,672
He always made sure he took his boxes.

151
00:05:39,739 --> 00:05:41,941
He never forgot to take his.

152
00:05:42,575 --> 00:05:45,645
He recently got himself another nickname

153
00:05:45,712 --> 00:05:47,313
<i>because of a single video.</i>

154
00:05:47,380 --> 00:05:50,683
<i>He was nicknamed</i>
<i>the chart-climbing soldier.</i>

155
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:52,652
Do you want to see
why he was nicknamed that?

156
00:05:52,719 --> 00:05:54,520
Let us show you a clip.

157
00:05:54,587 --> 00:05:56,789
This is one of Jin-young's videos.
Let's see it.

158
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:01,794
-How cool.
-It's this guy.

159
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:02,929
EMBARRASSED

160
00:06:02,995 --> 00:06:04,030
You're big.

161
00:06:04,097 --> 00:06:05,098
HERE HE GOES

162
00:06:05,164 --> 00:06:06,165
AMAZED

163
00:06:06,232 --> 00:06:07,233
AUTOMATIC AMAZEMENT

164
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:08,668
So he danced in the uniform.

165
00:06:09,535 --> 00:06:10,737
That's so awesome.

166
00:06:10,803 --> 00:06:12,238
-How does he move so freely?
-How cool.

167
00:06:12,305 --> 00:06:13,339
You're ripped.

168
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:15,475
Tecktonik moves.

169
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:16,809
That's so cool.

170
00:06:17,844 --> 00:06:18,845
He's such a good dancer.

171
00:06:18,911 --> 00:06:19,912
WATCHING CLOSELY

172
00:06:19,979 --> 00:06:21,748
Were you a private first class?

173
00:06:21,814 --> 00:06:23,216
-You're right.
-A PFC, right?

174
00:06:23,282 --> 00:06:24,684
-PFC in my third month.
-Third month?

175
00:06:24,751 --> 00:06:26,319
You can see bits of his face.

176
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:27,620
THE FINISHING TURN

177
00:06:27,687 --> 00:06:28,888
That was so awesome.

178
00:06:28,955 --> 00:06:30,923
EMBARRASSED

179
00:06:32,692 --> 00:06:34,026
What was that situation?

180
00:06:34,093 --> 00:06:36,629
It was at an event on Armed Forces Day,

181
00:06:36,696 --> 00:06:39,332
and the longest legally-allowed leave
was at stake,

182
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:40,566
-seven days.
-Really?

183
00:06:40,633 --> 00:06:42,135
-Seven days?
-Seven days, six nights.

184
00:06:42,201 --> 00:06:44,203
-Seven days, six nights?
-From the commander?

185
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:45,471
Seven days' leave is huge.

186
00:06:45,538 --> 00:06:47,206
You all get it, right?

187
00:06:47,273 --> 00:06:48,508
Yes, that's such a long leave.

188
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:51,043
-Gotta put your life at stake.
-My members reached out and said,

189
00:06:51,110 --> 00:06:52,412
"You tried harder than our concert."

190
00:06:53,446 --> 00:06:55,915
"If you performed at our concerts
with that much enthusiasm,

191
00:06:56,682 --> 00:06:58,618
you would've destroyed the stage."

192
00:07:02,121 --> 00:07:03,256
OH WELL, YOU KNOW?

193
00:07:04,323 --> 00:07:07,493
-You were ripped too. Have you worked out?
-Back then,

194
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,362
I had gained some weight.

195
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:11,731
Did you shed some weight
after getting discharged?

196
00:07:11,798 --> 00:07:13,666
Yes, I lost quite a lot.

197
00:07:13,733 --> 00:07:15,535
I had become 80 kg.

198
00:07:15,601 --> 00:07:16,769
How much did you lose?

199
00:07:16,836 --> 00:07:19,372
I had to drop 10 kg after my discharge.

200
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,907
Why did you lose weight at 80 kg?

201
00:07:20,973 --> 00:07:22,475
That's my dream weight.

202
00:07:23,376 --> 00:07:25,244
YOU LOOKED PERFECT

203
00:07:25,311 --> 00:07:26,813
You're going to be anemic.

204
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:29,015
That's my goal weight, 80 kg.

205
00:07:29,081 --> 00:07:30,883
You'll feel dizzy when you reach 80 kg.

206
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:32,652
It's my dream to be 80 kg.

207
00:07:33,219 --> 00:07:34,220
DIFFERENT VIEWS ON 80 KG

208
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:35,822
Yes, you looked perfect.

209
00:07:35,888 --> 00:07:37,323
The big ones think differently.

210
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:39,192
-"The big ones"?
-I hope I can be 80 kg.

211
00:07:39,258 --> 00:07:41,060
-Eighty sounds nice.
-That's perfect.

212
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,128
I want to live that life.

213
00:07:42,195 --> 00:07:44,497
-Things are so feisty here.
-They're in three digits.

214
00:07:44,564 --> 00:07:46,999
-You should stay alert.
-I really should.

215
00:07:47,066 --> 00:07:49,435
Actually, the Big Four,

216
00:07:49,502 --> 00:07:52,405
Ho-young, Poong, Nam-no, and Sung-jun,

217
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,574
-also had their smaller era.
-Of course.

218
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:56,876
-We weren't born this big.
-We weren't.

219
00:07:56,943 --> 00:07:58,444
-We weren't born like this.
-No.

220
00:07:58,511 --> 00:08:01,013
-They were also once like Jin-young.
-Of course.

221
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:03,850
We asked them for a picture
of their best-looking days,

222
00:08:03,916 --> 00:08:05,818
-and they did.
-What if they're too hot?

223
00:08:05,885 --> 00:08:07,453
-I'm looking forward to it.
-I'm not.

224
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,422
-Let's take a look.
-The Big Four.

225
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:10,490
THE BIG 4'S GLORY DAYS

226
00:08:10,556 --> 00:08:11,824
"The Big Four"?

227
00:08:11,891 --> 00:08:13,493
-There's Nam-no.
-Who's that?

228
00:08:13,559 --> 00:08:14,560
Look at him!

229
00:08:14,627 --> 00:08:16,762
Who's that on the right?

230
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:19,765
-What is that?
-He looks like Jung Jae-hyung.

231
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:21,033
You used to look like that?

232
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,869
-That's Sung-jun, right?
-He has deep-set eyes.

233
00:08:22,935 --> 00:08:24,136
Right? It's Sung-jun.

234
00:08:24,203 --> 00:08:26,239
That's from when I was studying abroad.

235
00:08:26,305 --> 00:08:27,974
-Is that Italy?
-That's Paris.

236
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,041
You were in Paris?

237
00:08:29,108 --> 00:08:32,245
-I went there like it was my neighborhood.
-Your neighborhood?

238
00:08:32,311 --> 00:08:34,847
-I visited often.
-Look at that hair.

239
00:08:34,914 --> 00:08:37,216
He looks like Jin-young
if you just look at his outfit.

240
00:08:37,283 --> 00:08:39,652
Not many can do that hair
unless you know you look good.

241
00:08:39,719 --> 00:08:41,020
-The Parisian style.
-Like the Seine?

242
00:08:41,087 --> 00:08:43,322
-The Parisian style.
-The big Parisian.

243
00:08:43,389 --> 00:08:44,390
He looks so different.

244
00:08:44,457 --> 00:08:46,325
-He does.
-When did you take these, Nam-no?

245
00:08:46,392 --> 00:08:48,261
I was 21 back then,

246
00:08:48,327 --> 00:08:49,595
and 18 in the middle.

247
00:08:49,662 --> 00:08:51,964
-You were 18?
-It wasn't during your military service?

248
00:08:52,031 --> 00:08:53,032
Something is quite wrong.

249
00:08:53,099 --> 00:08:55,067
Your uniform had some slack.

250
00:08:55,134 --> 00:08:58,371
-Back then, that apron was big on me.
-It was.

251
00:08:58,437 --> 00:08:59,438
You look good.

252
00:08:59,505 --> 00:09:00,973
And he wrapped the string around
a few times.

253
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:04,343
-I was popular back then.
-You were?

254
00:09:04,410 --> 00:09:06,546
Let's take a look
at Poong and Ho-young's best days.

255
00:09:06,612 --> 00:09:07,947
Poong and Ho-young.

256
00:09:08,014 --> 00:09:10,149
EVERYONE SOUNDS AMAZED

257
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:11,217
Not bad!

258
00:09:11,284 --> 00:09:12,385
Poong and Ho-young.

259
00:09:13,419 --> 00:09:15,154
LOOKING NICE

260
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:17,023
-Not bad.
-Why were you so thin?

261
00:09:17,089 --> 00:09:19,225
-He looks like Ha Jung-woo.
-Ha Jung-woo?

262
00:09:19,292 --> 00:09:20,693
-He had good vibes.
-I do see it a bit.

263
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:23,396
Were you trying to copy the look
from <i>I'm Sorry, I Love You</i>?

264
00:09:23,462 --> 00:09:26,732
-Yes, I can see that.
-You're dressed like So Ji-sub.

265
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:28,801
It was around 2003, I think.

266
00:09:28,868 --> 00:09:31,304
-That's over 20 years ago.
-Yes, 2003.

267
00:09:31,370 --> 00:09:33,472
-I was shooting an ad.
-An ad?

268
00:09:33,539 --> 00:09:35,241
You shot an ad in your twenties?

269
00:09:35,308 --> 00:09:37,243
-I can't believe that guy became this guy.
-Dang it.

270
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:38,311
Is this Ho-young?

271
00:09:38,377 --> 00:09:39,645
-This is Ho-young?
-Yes.

272
00:09:39,712 --> 00:09:42,248
-Yes, that's me.
-What happened?

273
00:09:42,315 --> 00:09:43,816
-Stop lying.
-I'm serious.

274
00:09:43,883 --> 00:09:44,884
-Really?
-How old were you?

275
00:09:44,951 --> 00:09:46,986
I was in seventh grade, I think.

276
00:09:47,053 --> 00:09:49,522
You didn't have your cooking sack yet.

277
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:52,191
-Back then…
-He could even hide behind that tree.

278
00:09:52,258 --> 00:09:54,060
WHERE'S HO-YOUNG?

279
00:09:54,126 --> 00:09:56,562
-He needs two trees now.
-Two trees?

280
00:09:56,629 --> 00:09:57,997
STILL NOT ENOUGH

281
00:09:58,064 --> 00:10:00,366
He'll need a 500-year-old tree.

282
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:02,101
I want to take a photo with the same tree.

283
00:10:02,168 --> 00:10:03,903
IT'LL HAVE TO BE THIS BIG

284
00:10:03,970 --> 00:10:06,939
-He'll need two trees to hide.
-Gosh.

285
00:10:07,006 --> 00:10:09,475
-Things are so feisty.
-His features were so defined.

286
00:10:09,542 --> 00:10:11,110
You must've been quite popular.

287
00:10:11,177 --> 00:10:12,979
I often got letters from older girls.

288
00:10:13,679 --> 00:10:14,680
From older girls?

289
00:10:14,747 --> 00:10:17,783
-You can get that big later in life?
-We hope to see you

290
00:10:17,850 --> 00:10:21,187
relive these glory days
while our show is still on air.

291
00:10:21,253 --> 00:10:23,923
-We want to see you become slimmer.
-Yes.

292
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:25,591
UNTIL THE DAY THE BIG 4 REACH 80 KG

293
00:10:25,658 --> 00:10:29,028
It's now time to look through
Jin-young's fridge.

294
00:10:29,095 --> 00:10:31,030
Take a look at what he keeps and find out

295
00:10:31,097 --> 00:10:34,734
-how you can change your diet.
-I'll learn from him.

296
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:37,236
Do you use this alone or with your family?

297
00:10:37,303 --> 00:10:38,738
-Alone. I live alone.
-Alone.

298
00:10:38,804 --> 00:10:40,873
-Do you not live with your parents?
-No.

299
00:10:40,940 --> 00:10:42,141
Where do they live?

300
00:10:42,208 --> 00:10:44,744
They live in Jinhae, South Gyeongsang-do.

301
00:10:44,810 --> 00:10:49,348
I moved to Seoul when I was 17,
and have lived away since then.

302
00:10:49,415 --> 00:10:53,319
From what I heard,
you spent your childhood on an island.

303
00:10:53,386 --> 00:10:56,455
There's a tiny island called U-do
within Jinhae.

304
00:10:56,522 --> 00:10:58,324
Not the one near Jeju-do.

305
00:10:58,391 --> 00:11:00,059
There's another U-do in Gyeongsang-do.

306
00:11:00,126 --> 00:11:02,662
<i>My grandparents lived there,</i>

307
00:11:02,728 --> 00:11:05,464
<i>so I always spent my time there</i>
<i>on the weekends.</i>

308
00:11:05,531 --> 00:11:07,700
You must've had lots of seafood.

309
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:10,569
-I had eel the most often.
-Eel?

310
00:11:10,636 --> 00:11:12,438
-Eel?
-I had it grilled

311
00:11:12,505 --> 00:11:14,173
with the sauce my father made.

312
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:16,342
Have you ever gone out fishing on a boat?

313
00:11:16,409 --> 00:11:19,145
-Yes, at night with my uncles.
-Night fishing.

314
00:11:19,211 --> 00:11:20,513
That's so romantic.

315
00:11:20,579 --> 00:11:22,281
You must use a dialect, then.

316
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:25,918
My friends who speak with a dialect say
I talk like a guy from Seoul,

317
00:11:25,985 --> 00:11:28,921
but when I try to lose the dialect,
it still shows a little.

318
00:11:28,988 --> 00:11:30,556
I'm kind of in-between.

319
00:11:30,623 --> 00:11:32,491
Hey, you've been doing well lately.

320
00:11:32,558 --> 00:11:33,893
<i>Still Shining</i> is fun to watch.

321
00:11:34,694 --> 00:11:36,696
-It is. It's a lot of fun.
-Right?

322
00:11:36,762 --> 00:11:38,397
-It's well-made.
-Yes, you say it when you hear it.

323
00:11:38,464 --> 00:11:40,700
-He just went with it.
-When someone else does it?

324
00:11:40,766 --> 00:11:43,069
You don't do it
unless the other person does it.

325
00:11:43,135 --> 00:11:44,837
Why don't we look through his fridge?

326
00:11:44,904 --> 00:11:47,139
What have we got here today?

327
00:11:47,206 --> 00:11:48,641
-Is it full of seafood?
-You know,

328
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,609
as soon as we open the doors…

329
00:11:50,676 --> 00:11:52,678
We'll see all of U-do inside.

330
00:11:53,079 --> 00:11:54,080
RISING EXPECTATIONS

331
00:11:54,146 --> 00:11:55,681
He'll have lumps of seaweed.

332
00:11:55,748 --> 00:11:57,583
-We can use it as a carpet.
-Yes.

333
00:11:57,650 --> 00:11:59,351
Blue crabs will crawl out,

334
00:11:59,418 --> 00:12:00,986
and eels will wriggle around.

335
00:12:01,253 --> 00:12:02,488
EYES SHUT

336
00:12:02,555 --> 00:12:03,556
An island boy.

337
00:12:03,622 --> 00:12:05,791
-We present Jin-young's fridge!
-Fridge!

338
00:12:06,425 --> 00:12:08,961
HUH?

339
00:12:09,361 --> 00:12:11,664
PRESENTING JIN-YOUNG'S FRIDGE

340
00:12:12,231 --> 00:12:15,367
-You can see he has some meat on top.
-He does.

341
00:12:15,434 --> 00:12:17,303
I'm sure it's hidden somewhere.

342
00:12:17,369 --> 00:12:18,738
NO SEAFOOD IN SIGHT YET

343
00:12:19,004 --> 00:12:20,706
-Let's start here. Wait.
-Rice?

344
00:12:20,773 --> 00:12:23,542
-Is this how you keep your rice?
-Rice?

345
00:12:23,609 --> 00:12:25,911
When my mom stops by,

346
00:12:25,978 --> 00:12:29,381
-she keeps them like that for me.
-Only as much as he'll eat.

347
00:12:29,448 --> 00:12:32,151
I see something else in here.
Wait, this entire basket

348
00:12:32,218 --> 00:12:33,719
is full of chicken breasts.

349
00:12:33,786 --> 00:12:36,322
-He stays on a diet.
-You must've had these to lose 10 kg.

350
00:12:36,388 --> 00:12:38,190
Chicken breast was all I ate,

351
00:12:38,257 --> 00:12:39,258
three meals a day.

352
00:12:39,325 --> 00:12:41,193
-For all three meals?
-All three meals?

353
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:44,096
I'm sure you have a secret
to continue eating chicken breast

354
00:12:44,163 --> 00:12:46,799
without getting too sick of it.

355
00:12:46,866 --> 00:12:48,434
I often made it into soup.

356
00:12:48,501 --> 00:12:50,369
-Soup?
-Yes.

357
00:12:50,436 --> 00:12:52,872
You slice the chicken breast, throw it in,

358
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:55,674
<i>add some mixed vegetables,</i>

359
00:12:55,741 --> 00:12:58,511
<i>and season with chicken stock</i>
<i>and sesame oil.</i>

360
00:12:58,577 --> 00:13:01,580
-A variation of a veggie soup.
-Yes.

361
00:13:01,647 --> 00:13:04,617
-I found some meat. It looks like pork.
-What's that?

362
00:13:04,683 --> 00:13:05,885
It's for <i>suyuk</i>, boiled pork.

363
00:13:05,951 --> 00:13:08,420
-It's for <i>suyuk</i>? Do you boil this?
-Oh, I see.

364
00:13:08,487 --> 00:13:12,057
My mom is a good cook,
so I learned an easy recipe from her.

365
00:13:12,124 --> 00:13:13,759
So do you cook?

366
00:13:13,826 --> 00:13:15,494
-Moderately.
-Moderately.

367
00:13:15,561 --> 00:13:17,096
I watch videos online and copy them.

368
00:13:17,163 --> 00:13:18,731
I guess I try to cook

369
00:13:18,798 --> 00:13:20,699
because I've lived alone for a while.

370
00:13:20,766 --> 00:13:22,568
I see some <i>jjajang</i> sauce,
black bean sauce.

371
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:23,869
Do you enjoy Chinese food?

372
00:13:23,936 --> 00:13:25,871
-I do.
-Those look good.

373
00:13:25,938 --> 00:13:29,008
What's your favorite dish?
People often say sweet and sour pork.

374
00:13:29,074 --> 00:13:30,376
-I love Dongpo pork.
-Dongpo pork?

375
00:13:30,442 --> 00:13:31,443
I love it.

376
00:13:31,510 --> 00:13:33,279
-He loves Dongpo pork.
-Make it for him.

377
00:13:33,345 --> 00:13:34,880
-I should.
-Back in the army,

378
00:13:34,947 --> 00:13:37,183
there was frozen Dongpo pork.

379
00:13:37,249 --> 00:13:40,553
It came out while that cooking show
was a huge hit.

380
00:13:40,619 --> 00:13:41,987
-<i>Frozen?</i>
-<i>At the post exchange.</i>

381
00:13:42,054 --> 00:13:43,389
-<i>At the post exchange?</i>
-<i>Yes.</i>

382
00:13:43,455 --> 00:13:45,357
-They had a frozen product?
-They did.

383
00:13:45,424 --> 00:13:46,992
<i>Eun-yeong made Dongpo pork dumplings</i>

384
00:13:47,059 --> 00:13:49,061
-<i>when you competed in</i> CCW1<i>.</i>
-<i>I did.</i>

385
00:13:49,128 --> 00:13:50,763
-I tried your frozen dumplings.
-You did?

386
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:51,831
They were good.

387
00:13:52,798 --> 00:13:55,267
-The <i>mala</i> flavor one.
-<i>Mala</i> flavor? That's a good one.

388
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:58,270
She must've been popular
among the soldiers.

389
00:14:02,741 --> 00:14:03,809
AH…

390
00:14:03,876 --> 00:14:05,911
-No, wait.
-You weren't popular!

391
00:14:05,978 --> 00:14:07,213
It's not that.

392
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:08,848
HE SAID NO

393
00:14:08,914 --> 00:14:11,050
You're the type who can't lie.

394
00:14:11,116 --> 00:14:13,919
That wasn't what I meant.
Will you please hear me out?

395
00:14:13,986 --> 00:14:15,788
-This is too funny.
-Please hear me out.

396
00:14:15,855 --> 00:14:17,890
The pause was too long.

397
00:14:17,957 --> 00:14:20,459
Her food was extremely popular.

398
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:21,660
But not the person?

399
00:14:21,727 --> 00:14:23,662
MOCKING LAUGHTER ON

400
00:14:23,729 --> 00:14:26,232
We didn't have much time
to be on our phones.

401
00:14:26,298 --> 00:14:28,033
-I see. Sure.
-You were very popular.

402
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:30,469
A chef should be happy
if their food is popular.

403
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:32,238
-Of course.
-That's even better, actually.

404
00:14:32,304 --> 00:14:34,106
-That's a compliment for a chef.
-It is.

405
00:14:34,173 --> 00:14:36,141
-It's all right.
-But not the person.

406
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:37,743
-He's easy to tease.
-He is.

407
00:14:37,810 --> 00:14:38,978
You were really popular.

408
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:40,112
Nice try, Eun-yeong.

409
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:42,715
-Your dumplings were good, anyway.
-Yes, that's what's important.

410
00:14:42,781 --> 00:14:45,584
-He has blueberries.
-We're only joking.

411
00:14:45,651 --> 00:14:47,186
What's this?

412
00:14:47,253 --> 00:14:50,122
-Greek yogurt my mom made.
-Yogurt?

413
00:14:50,189 --> 00:14:52,358
-She made this for you?
-Yes.

414
00:14:52,424 --> 00:14:55,227
I eat that with frozen blueberries
for breakfast.

415
00:14:55,294 --> 00:14:57,563
-And these.
-What are these containers?

416
00:14:57,630 --> 00:14:59,665
It's about time we see some seafood.

417
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:00,733
A container of eels?

418
00:15:00,799 --> 00:15:02,601
-It's kimchi.
-A container of eels?

419
00:15:03,369 --> 00:15:04,637
NOT EELS BUT KIMCHI

420
00:15:04,703 --> 00:15:07,172
She sends you this much kimchi?

421
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:08,974
-Is this from your mother?
-Yes, she made it.

422
00:15:09,808 --> 00:15:11,410
MOTHER'S KIMCHI

423
00:15:11,477 --> 00:15:12,645
She made it this season.

424
00:15:12,711 --> 00:15:15,147
In this season. Do you like kimchi?

425
00:15:15,214 --> 00:15:17,416
-I love it.
-It looks red and delicious.

426
00:15:17,483 --> 00:15:18,751
-It looks good.
-I love it.

427
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:20,986
Should we make some instant rice?

428
00:15:21,053 --> 00:15:23,022
Do you make
braised pork and kimchi with this?

429
00:15:23,088 --> 00:15:24,490
I just eat it as is.

430
00:15:24,556 --> 00:15:26,759
-Just kimchi?
-I want to make something,

431
00:15:26,825 --> 00:15:28,794
but delivery food's great these days.

432
00:15:29,662 --> 00:15:31,897
What do you often get delivered?

433
00:15:31,964 --> 00:15:33,632
Eel over rice.

434
00:15:33,699 --> 00:15:36,535
-You must love eel.
-He really loves eel.

435
00:15:36,602 --> 00:15:38,203
I eat it at least once a week.

436
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:39,738
-Once a week?
-Eel over rice.

437
00:15:39,805 --> 00:15:41,440
-We might see some eel.
-Yes.

438
00:15:41,507 --> 00:15:42,775
He has to have some.

439
00:15:42,841 --> 00:15:45,010
I'm sure it's somewhere in here.

440
00:15:45,077 --> 00:15:47,947
-And what's here? Yes.
-Vegetables.

441
00:15:48,013 --> 00:15:49,715
I found cilantro.

442
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:52,151
He has two containers of these.

443
00:15:52,217 --> 00:15:54,119
-I really love cilantro.
-You do?

444
00:15:54,186 --> 00:15:55,587
I really love it.

445
00:15:55,654 --> 00:15:58,424
-I need it with Thai food.
-With Thai food.

446
00:15:58,490 --> 00:16:00,726
I just eat it raw.

447
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:02,962
-Carrots.
-These are well-prepped.

448
00:16:03,028 --> 00:16:06,231
My mom said I should slice those
and throw them into salads.

449
00:16:06,298 --> 00:16:08,400
-I love those too.
-You do? He loves carrots.

450
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:10,602
-He has more carrots down there.
-He does.

451
00:16:10,669 --> 00:16:12,438
He has more carrots here.

452
00:16:12,504 --> 00:16:13,672
Do you keep a horse?

453
00:16:13,739 --> 00:16:15,140
-No.
-Just checking.

454
00:16:15,207 --> 00:16:16,909
-He may keep a pet horse.
-Sure.

455
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:18,043
Do you keep a pet?

456
00:16:18,110 --> 00:16:19,511
-A horse?
-I live in an apartment unit.

457
00:16:19,578 --> 00:16:20,980
He has a big stash of carrots.

458
00:16:21,046 --> 00:16:22,381
-It's good.
-The freezer.

459
00:16:22,448 --> 00:16:23,449
Is that eel?

460
00:16:23,515 --> 00:16:25,184
-It's not eel.
-It's not.

461
00:16:25,250 --> 00:16:26,685
It's meat.

462
00:16:26,752 --> 00:16:28,454
-Red meat.
-Beef brisket.

463
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:29,521
These look nice.

464
00:16:29,588 --> 00:16:30,889
-They look fresh.
-Nice color.

465
00:16:30,956 --> 00:16:34,827
My mom knows a place
that cuts fresh meat after butchering.

466
00:16:34,893 --> 00:16:36,862
She gets it from there
and sends it right away.

467
00:16:36,929 --> 00:16:38,664
These were freshly butchered
and sent to him.

468
00:16:38,731 --> 00:16:40,132
They look really nice.

469
00:16:40,199 --> 00:16:43,268
As we speak, I have finally found
some seafood, some fish.

470
00:16:43,335 --> 00:16:45,404
-Eel?
-I found some seafood.

471
00:16:45,471 --> 00:16:46,772
-Tonguefish.
-Mackerel?

472
00:16:46,839 --> 00:16:48,540
-Mackerel.
-Mackerel.

473
00:16:48,607 --> 00:16:50,175
-Mackerel.
-Is that eel?

474
00:16:50,242 --> 00:16:51,443
-Mackerel.
-They're all mackerels.

475
00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:52,511
-Mackerel.
-Eel.

476
00:16:52,578 --> 00:16:53,912
-These are all mackerels.
-What?

477
00:16:53,979 --> 00:16:55,547
WHERE ARE YOUR EELS?

478
00:16:55,614 --> 00:16:57,583
It's too tough to prep eels.

479
00:16:57,649 --> 00:17:00,686
-That's true.
-So I can't really cook it myself.

480
00:17:00,753 --> 00:17:03,822
That's why he only has mackerels,
which are easier to prep.

481
00:17:03,889 --> 00:17:07,226
He barely has any seafood.

482
00:17:07,292 --> 00:17:08,894
Next, some sweet potatoes.

483
00:17:08,961 --> 00:17:09,962
CONTINUES TO BROWSE

484
00:17:11,163 --> 00:17:13,031
What's that? Food waste?

485
00:17:13,098 --> 00:17:14,933
-It looks like food waste.
-What's that?

486
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,402
Maybe green onion. Is it food waste?

487
00:17:16,468 --> 00:17:18,437
-It looks like it.
-No way.

488
00:17:18,504 --> 00:17:20,539
-He wouldn't do that.
-He kept it frozen.

489
00:17:20,606 --> 00:17:23,942
-Is this leftover food?
-That's my mom's <i>japchae</i>.

490
00:17:24,009 --> 00:17:27,279
-It's his mother's <i>japchae</i>!
-You called it food waste!

491
00:17:27,346 --> 00:17:30,282
-It's <i>japchae</i>!
-You're also rude with every breath.

492
00:17:30,349 --> 00:17:31,950
That's so awful.

493
00:17:32,017 --> 00:17:33,986
You're so rude with every breath you take!

494
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:35,054
-So rude!
-How awful!

495
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:37,289
-Sit down!
-Is it <i>japchae</i>?

496
00:17:37,356 --> 00:17:38,857
-Leave!
-It has veggies too.

497
00:17:38,924 --> 00:17:41,226
-Is this really <i>japchae</i>?
-Is it?

498
00:17:41,293 --> 00:17:43,195
This is super delicious <i>japchae</i>.

499
00:17:43,262 --> 00:17:46,298
-It's super delicious <i>japchae</i>!
-He must be heartbroken.

500
00:17:46,365 --> 00:17:49,134
I could chow this down as is
if I were asked to.

501
00:17:49,201 --> 00:17:51,770
-Me too.
-She made it deliciously with care!

502
00:17:51,837 --> 00:17:54,907
-It's his mother's <i>japchae</i>.
-My mouth is watering!

503
00:17:54,973 --> 00:17:57,176
Am I the only piece of trash here?

504
00:17:58,444 --> 00:18:00,245
You also thought it was food waste!

505
00:18:01,013 --> 00:18:02,481
I'm sorry, ma'am.

506
00:18:02,548 --> 00:18:04,349
I didn't recognize it.

507
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:06,185
How can you call this waste?

508
00:18:06,685 --> 00:18:08,120
Our son loves <i>japchae</i>.

509
00:18:08,187 --> 00:18:10,456
All of a sudden, it's "our" son?

510
00:18:10,522 --> 00:18:13,258
-We almost got canceled today.
-Almost.

511
00:18:13,325 --> 00:18:14,927
-What's this?
-Green onion.

512
00:18:14,993 --> 00:18:16,361
-You prepped them.
-My mom does that too.

513
00:18:16,428 --> 00:18:18,430
I chopped them

514
00:18:18,497 --> 00:18:20,299
<i>to use them with beef over rice</i>

515
00:18:20,365 --> 00:18:21,767
-that I sometimes make.
-Beef over rice?

516
00:18:21,834 --> 00:18:24,670
It was delicious
to make oil with some green onion.

517
00:18:24,736 --> 00:18:26,171
And he chopped these himself.

518
00:18:26,238 --> 00:18:27,840
Anyway, make something delicious for him.

519
00:18:27,906 --> 00:18:29,575
That was all for Jin-young's fridge!

520
00:18:29,641 --> 00:18:32,144
DONE CHECKING OUT JIN-YOUNG'S FRIDGE

521
00:18:32,211 --> 00:18:35,881
We looked through the ingredients
Jin-young keeps in his fridge.

522
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:38,617
It's time to find out his orders.

523
00:18:38,684 --> 00:18:40,953
What does he want to eat today?

524
00:18:41,019 --> 00:18:42,621
Here's the first order.

525
00:18:43,555 --> 00:18:45,290
-A Flashy Dish.
-A Flashy Dish.

526
00:18:45,357 --> 00:18:46,391
Flashy.

527
00:18:46,458 --> 00:18:47,826
-Flashy.
-It's in a dialect, right?

528
00:18:47,893 --> 00:18:51,563
-It means you're showing off your style.
-It's a dialect.

529
00:18:51,630 --> 00:18:55,868
-You're kind of flashy today.
-You're flashy.

530
00:18:55,934 --> 00:18:57,669
-You're flashy. Just like that.
-A Flashy Dish.

531
00:18:57,736 --> 00:19:00,839
Can you elaborate and tell our chefs
what you're looking for?

532
00:19:00,906 --> 00:19:03,775
I usually only eat dishes
that are simple to make,

533
00:19:03,842 --> 00:19:06,478
so I've never had anything spectacular
made by a chef.

534
00:19:06,545 --> 00:19:08,647
-Something very fancy.
-Like, "wow."

535
00:19:08,714 --> 00:19:11,550
-Something that looks great at one look.
-Something fancy.

536
00:19:11,617 --> 00:19:15,120
A Flashy Dish,
something that only chefs could make.

537
00:19:15,187 --> 00:19:17,322
What's his second order?

538
00:19:17,389 --> 00:19:18,891
CARROT HEAVEN

539
00:19:18,957 --> 00:19:21,160
-I knew this would happen.
-I knew it.

540
00:19:21,226 --> 00:19:23,562
-There was Carrot Hell in <i>CCW2</i>.
-Carrot Hell.

541
00:19:23,629 --> 00:19:24,997
It was called Carrot Hell then,

542
00:19:25,063 --> 00:19:26,632
but this is Carrot Heaven.

543
00:19:26,698 --> 00:19:29,601
Yes, I had to do that round,
so I'm glad I went with Yu-jin's fridge.

544
00:19:30,102 --> 00:19:31,503
THE UNFORGETTABLE CARROT HELL

545
00:19:31,570 --> 00:19:33,238
The only carrot dish I've had

546
00:19:33,305 --> 00:19:35,841
-was carrot <i>râpées</i>, French carrot salad.
-Carrot <i>râpées</i>.

547
00:19:35,908 --> 00:19:37,543
I have too many carrots at home,

548
00:19:37,609 --> 00:19:40,679
so what else can I make with those?

549
00:19:40,746 --> 00:19:42,014
Something new.

550
00:19:43,248 --> 00:19:44,283
Okay then.

551
00:19:44,349 --> 00:19:47,052
Other than the four who cooked previously
with Yu-jin's ingredients,

552
00:19:47,119 --> 00:19:50,989
we have Hyun-suk, Sam,
Poong, and Si-hyeon left.

553
00:19:51,056 --> 00:19:54,326
It's Si-hyeon's first time here,
so she should get the first pick.

554
00:19:54,393 --> 00:19:56,662
Yes, we can help out with that.

555
00:19:56,728 --> 00:19:59,831
I was in <i>CCW2</i>,
but I never got to Carrot Hell.

556
00:19:59,898 --> 00:20:02,568
So I thought it would be great
if I could cook with carrots

557
00:20:02,634 --> 00:20:04,603
and make something I imagined,
but what do I do?

558
00:20:04,970 --> 00:20:06,205
THE FIRST-TIMER IS SUPER NERVOUS

559
00:20:06,271 --> 00:20:08,707
-I'll go with Carrot Heaven.
-Carrot Heaven.

560
00:20:08,774 --> 00:20:10,876
Carrot Heaven. Okay.

561
00:20:10,943 --> 00:20:13,478
Well, the production crew
asked Little Tiger

562
00:20:13,545 --> 00:20:16,014
whom she wanted to fight first.

563
00:20:16,081 --> 00:20:17,649
-An easy fight.
-Who is it?

564
00:20:17,716 --> 00:20:19,484
She singled out Webtoon Artist Poong.

565
00:20:19,551 --> 00:20:21,520
-I get it. Me too.
-I was just like her.

566
00:20:21,587 --> 00:20:23,288
I think Chef Poong's dishes--

567
00:20:23,355 --> 00:20:24,389
-I'm not a chef.
-Right.

568
00:20:24,456 --> 00:20:25,824
-A webtoon artist.
-The artist.

569
00:20:25,891 --> 00:20:27,292
I always get excited to watch

570
00:20:27,359 --> 00:20:30,495
-what Artist Poong makes every week.
-"What will he make?"

571
00:20:30,562 --> 00:20:31,897
I get so curious.

572
00:20:31,964 --> 00:20:33,865
-He's so unpredictable. Exactly
-"What will Poong make?"

573
00:20:33,932 --> 00:20:36,201
Poong, show her
what <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> is truly like.

574
00:20:36,268 --> 00:20:38,170
-All right.
-I think I picked the wrong guy.

575
00:20:38,237 --> 00:20:39,938
-He's a true beast.
-I'll make sure

576
00:20:40,005 --> 00:20:42,841
she gets utterly shocked.

577
00:20:45,010 --> 00:20:46,678
OH, MY

578
00:20:46,745 --> 00:20:48,480
This will be fun. It's a big match.

579
00:20:48,547 --> 00:20:52,084
Little Tiger versus Old Beastly Dude.

580
00:20:52,150 --> 00:20:54,553
That means Sam will fight Hyun-suk.

581
00:20:54,620 --> 00:20:58,457
The two amazing Western chefs
are going to make something flashy.

582
00:20:58,523 --> 00:21:01,426
A flashy dish, a fancy dish.

583
00:21:01,593 --> 00:21:02,694
TRYING NOT TO LAUGH

584
00:21:02,761 --> 00:21:04,229
I've always been doing that.

585
00:21:04,296 --> 00:21:05,597
That's true.

586
00:21:05,664 --> 00:21:08,233
There are people who seem flashy
without even trying.

587
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:10,535
And that is someone like Chef Jong-won.

588
00:21:11,503 --> 00:21:13,071
-Certainly, it's Chef Jong-won.
-Right.

589
00:21:13,138 --> 00:21:14,640
Please look forward to that.

590
00:21:14,706 --> 00:21:15,874
And now,

591
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:19,544
let Hyun-suk and Sam begin
their 15-minute cook-off!

592
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:22,914
THE FIRST ROUND BEGINS NOW

593
00:21:22,981 --> 00:21:27,586
<i>This is the first cook-off</i>
<i>played with Jin-young's ingredients.</i>

594
00:21:27,653 --> 00:21:30,522
A man who went to the dark side
with his grade school fans on his back,

595
00:21:30,589 --> 00:21:33,859
the Flashy Canine, Chef Sam,

596
00:21:33,925 --> 00:21:36,728
versus a man who'll soon carry
his grandchild on his back…

597
00:21:38,163 --> 00:21:39,331
That's true.

598
00:21:39,398 --> 00:21:42,601
…the Flashy Grandpa, Chef Hyun-suk.

599
00:21:42,668 --> 00:21:44,636
-They're the rivals with history.
-They are.

600
00:21:44,703 --> 00:21:47,172
Chef Hyun-suk had
very showy results in the previous season.

601
00:21:47,239 --> 00:21:50,309
<i>Not only did he win the regular season,</i>
<i>but he also became the champion.</i>

602
00:21:50,375 --> 00:21:52,778
<i>On top of that,</i>
<i>during our awards ceremony,</i>

603
00:21:52,844 --> 00:21:56,148
<i>he took the Best Dish Award</i>
<i>as voted by our chefs.</i>

604
00:21:56,214 --> 00:21:58,917
You can say that
he won two Grand Awards last year.

605
00:21:58,984 --> 00:22:02,087
He has had great results
because he never lost twice in a row.

606
00:22:02,154 --> 00:22:03,488
However, currently,

607
00:22:03,555 --> 00:22:07,192
you have lost both previous rounds
against him.

608
00:22:07,259 --> 00:22:10,195
<i>He lost twice in a row.</i>

609
00:22:10,262 --> 00:22:12,664
Chef Sam, what was your goal
in the 2026 season?

610
00:22:13,231 --> 00:22:15,934
-To fight in the final match.
-The finals.

611
00:22:16,001 --> 00:22:18,070
Can we expect to see
three consecutive wins?

612
00:22:18,136 --> 00:22:20,906
It's a tempting record,
so I'll do my best.

613
00:22:21,173 --> 00:22:22,341
GOOD LUCK

614
00:22:22,407 --> 00:22:24,943
The order is named A Flashy Dish,

615
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:28,847
so you must make something fancy
with a nice presentation.

616
00:22:28,914 --> 00:22:32,351
-We received another greenroom recording.
-What is it?

617
00:22:32,417 --> 00:22:35,987
-Chef Hyun-suk said this quietly.
-What did he say?

618
00:22:36,054 --> 00:22:39,024
"Sam pretends like he doesn't care,

619
00:22:39,091 --> 00:22:41,159
but he goes around acting flashy."

620
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:43,228
OH

621
00:22:43,295 --> 00:22:45,464
Unlike how he seems,

622
00:22:45,530 --> 00:22:50,001
he's quite interested
in looking fancy and flashy.

623
00:22:50,068 --> 00:22:52,637
-Really?
-He's really into watches…

624
00:22:52,704 --> 00:22:55,107
-Watches, yes.
-…especially brand-name watches.

625
00:22:55,173 --> 00:22:57,709
-He has lots of expensive watches.
-Right.

626
00:22:57,776 --> 00:22:58,910
Yes, he has nice watches.

627
00:22:58,977 --> 00:23:00,445
If you don't have a watch,
he won't talk to you.

628
00:23:00,846 --> 00:23:01,947
WHOA

629
00:23:02,013 --> 00:23:03,582
-He checks your wrist?
-He checks that?

630
00:23:03,648 --> 00:23:06,184
Jin-young was rather surprised
at Hyun-suk's report.

631
00:23:06,251 --> 00:23:08,153
He didn't think Sam was like that.

632
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:11,790
But those who have been flashy
can make something flashy.

633
00:23:12,691 --> 00:23:14,693
-That's true.
-That's right.

634
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:16,962
He knows the vibe he's going for.

635
00:23:17,028 --> 00:23:18,997
A FLASHY LINE

636
00:23:19,064 --> 00:23:22,467
There are people
who need items to look flashy.

637
00:23:22,534 --> 00:23:25,270
Then there are others
who look flashy without trying.

638
00:23:25,837 --> 00:23:29,408
-Someone like Chef Jong-won.
-As always.

639
00:23:31,943 --> 00:23:34,946
-We also have something that Sam said.
-What is it?

640
00:23:35,013 --> 00:23:38,917
"You can describe
Hyun-suk's dishes with this saying."

641
00:23:39,451 --> 00:23:40,719
"Empty vessels make the most noise."

642
00:23:42,721 --> 00:23:43,855
OH MY GOD

643
00:23:44,289 --> 00:23:45,524
SWAG

644
00:23:45,590 --> 00:23:47,559
Rattle, rattle.

645
00:23:47,626 --> 00:23:48,794
Do you admit to saying this?

646
00:23:48,860 --> 00:23:50,328
I said those exact words.

647
00:23:50,395 --> 00:23:53,298
See? We never lie about these reports.

648
00:23:53,365 --> 00:23:55,066
HE SERIOUSLY HAS BECOME DARK

649
00:23:55,133 --> 00:23:56,535
-May I add a word?
-Sure.

650
00:23:56,601 --> 00:23:59,438
I have had the most wins
in the 2025 season.

651
00:23:59,504 --> 00:24:02,574
So he's saying the guests who voted for me

652
00:24:02,641 --> 00:24:05,343
all chose an empty vessel.

653
00:24:07,813 --> 00:24:09,481
Gosh, he's so petty.

654
00:24:09,548 --> 00:24:11,550
He's become so petty.

655
00:24:11,616 --> 00:24:13,585
He became a petty grandpa.

656
00:24:13,652 --> 00:24:15,353
-How petty.
-What do you mean?

657
00:24:15,420 --> 00:24:16,621
-It was a joke.
-Exactly.

658
00:24:16,988 --> 00:24:19,157
BOO, GRANDPA

659
00:24:19,224 --> 00:24:20,625
Boo. That was so uncool.

660
00:24:20,692 --> 00:24:22,794
I'LL MINCE YOU, MAN

661
00:24:22,861 --> 00:24:24,129
Who are you, Thor?

662
00:24:24,963 --> 00:24:27,032
CHEF SAM'S INGREDIENTS:
PORK FOR BOILING, STRIP LOIN

663
00:24:27,098 --> 00:24:29,134
CILANTRO, CABBAGE,
BUTTERHEAD LETTUCE, OYSTER SAUCE

664
00:24:29,201 --> 00:24:31,636
The dish I'm going to make is this.

665
00:24:31,703 --> 00:24:34,606
Stop, You've Won Enough Times.

666
00:24:35,006 --> 00:24:36,575
THE DARK SAM NOW SPEAKS IN A DIALECT

667
00:24:36,641 --> 00:24:38,944
-Stop it.
-Boom, boom, boom!

668
00:24:39,010 --> 00:24:41,179
It's a reference to a line
from the film, <i>Friend</i>.

669
00:24:41,246 --> 00:24:44,349
In the rain, he goes, "I had enough."

670
00:24:44,416 --> 00:24:45,984
Can you do it for us, Jin-young?

671
00:24:46,551 --> 00:24:48,220
Stop, You've Won Enough Times.

672
00:24:48,420 --> 00:24:49,688
WOW

673
00:24:50,155 --> 00:24:51,690
A FLASHY VOICE

674
00:24:51,756 --> 00:24:53,992
Of course. Actors always deliver.

675
00:24:54,493 --> 00:24:55,660
EMBARRASSED

676
00:24:55,727 --> 00:24:58,096
I want to transform the ingredients

677
00:24:58,163 --> 00:25:00,365
you always enjoyed into my own style

678
00:25:00,432 --> 00:25:01,933
and let you eat something new.

679
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:05,136
I'll make a sauce called chimichurri,

680
00:25:05,203 --> 00:25:08,106
-which goes well with meat or veggies.
-He has cilantro.

681
00:25:08,173 --> 00:25:09,641
You said you liked <i>suyuk</i>, boiled pork,

682
00:25:09,708 --> 00:25:13,678
-so I'll pair that with chimichurri.
-Chimichurri is delicious.

683
00:25:13,745 --> 00:25:16,681
Also, I'll make hot stone pot rice,
but not the usual kind.

684
00:25:16,748 --> 00:25:20,719
I'll make it with a huge pile of cilantro.

685
00:25:20,785 --> 00:25:22,487
-Cilantro hot stone pot rice?
-Cilantro rice.

686
00:25:22,554 --> 00:25:24,289
-Whoa.
-Sounds awesome.

687
00:25:24,356 --> 00:25:25,757
My kick is in the new experience.

688
00:25:25,824 --> 00:25:30,128
I interpreted flashiness
as giving you a new kind of flavor.

689
00:25:30,962 --> 00:25:32,864
CHEF HYUN-SUK'S INGREDIENTS:
BONELESS RIB, CHICKEN BREAST

690
00:25:32,931 --> 00:25:35,133
CILANTRO, DOENJANG, BALSAMIC VINEGAR,
OYSTER SAUCE, BONITO POWDER

691
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:37,102
Here's the name of my dish.

692
00:25:37,402 --> 00:25:39,204
PULLING OUT

693
00:25:39,271 --> 00:25:40,705
-A fan?
-Is he a hermit in the mountains?

694
00:25:41,006 --> 00:25:42,140
WHOOP

695
00:25:43,174 --> 00:25:44,242
Fan Master Choi.

696
00:25:44,309 --> 00:25:46,578
-Fan Master Choi.
-Choi.

697
00:25:46,645 --> 00:25:48,313
-Fan Master Choi?
-Fan Master Choi.

698
00:25:48,380 --> 00:25:50,248
FLUTTER

699
00:25:50,315 --> 00:25:51,516
That's cool.

700
00:25:51,583 --> 00:25:54,486
-He looks cool with his long arms.
-What will you do with that fan?

701
00:25:54,553 --> 00:25:56,187
-He looks cool with his long arms.
-Yes.

702
00:25:56,254 --> 00:25:58,456
-He kept mentioning eels.
-Yes.

703
00:25:58,523 --> 00:26:01,326
So I'm going to make eel over rice.

704
00:26:01,393 --> 00:26:02,961
-But…
-He doesn't have any eels.

705
00:26:03,028 --> 00:26:05,830
-I don't have any eel.
-There weren't any eels.

706
00:26:05,897 --> 00:26:08,533
Have I ever stopped cooking a dish
because there was no ingredient?

707
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,768
-He'll make eel?
-He will?

708
00:26:09,834 --> 00:26:10,869
How will you do that?

709
00:26:10,936 --> 00:26:14,239
-He doesn't have any eels.
-How are you going to do that?

710
00:26:14,306 --> 00:26:15,941
There aren't any eels in the fridge,

711
00:26:16,007 --> 00:26:19,744
but I'll make something
that'll taste just like eel over rice.

712
00:26:20,312 --> 00:26:22,547
Is that all you're making? Anything else?

713
00:26:22,614 --> 00:26:25,483
Eel over rice is always served with soup,

714
00:26:25,550 --> 00:26:28,787
so I'll show you
how to make delicious soup

715
00:26:28,853 --> 00:26:30,722
-in just one minute.
-In just a minute?

716
00:26:30,789 --> 00:26:32,991
We'll make sure we time that minute.

717
00:26:33,325 --> 00:26:35,360
EXTRA STRICT

718
00:26:35,427 --> 00:26:39,230
He says too many flashy lines
he can't fulfill.

719
00:26:39,297 --> 00:26:41,499
And for this round,

720
00:26:41,566 --> 00:26:44,936
why don't we have Yu-jin help us
with the five-minute interim check?

721
00:26:45,003 --> 00:26:46,271
-I'd love to.
-Is that all right?

722
00:26:46,338 --> 00:26:47,405
-Yes.
-All right.

723
00:26:47,472 --> 00:26:50,175
Yu-jin does an excellent job
with hosting shows too.

724
00:26:50,241 --> 00:26:55,480
And now, you'll begin cooking
two flashy dishes for Jin-young.

725
00:26:55,547 --> 00:26:58,149
This man wishes
to blow Sam away with his fan.

726
00:26:58,216 --> 00:27:01,052
Fan Master Choi, Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

727
00:27:01,119 --> 00:27:03,922
But this man will
bite Hyun-suk with his canine teeth.

728
00:27:03,989 --> 00:27:07,192
Canine Master, Chef Sam Kim.

729
00:27:07,258 --> 00:27:10,762
Which one of them
will be the flashiest chef of the show?

730
00:27:10,829 --> 00:27:14,399
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

731
00:27:14,466 --> 00:27:15,700
You got this!

732
00:27:16,267 --> 00:27:18,203
He's looking for A Flashy Dish.

733
00:27:18,269 --> 00:27:20,705
-Begin!
-You got this!

734
00:27:21,673 --> 00:27:23,675
He's looking for A Flashy Dish.

735
00:27:23,742 --> 00:27:25,810
Come on. Look at him.

736
00:27:26,244 --> 00:27:28,913
STARTS OFF WITH A SURPRISE FLASHY MOVE

737
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:32,083
His pose is already flashy
with one hand behind his back.

738
00:27:32,717 --> 00:27:34,719
I thought you were a sommelier.

739
00:27:34,786 --> 00:27:38,523
It's because he has a bad back.
He has to keep one hand there.

740
00:27:38,590 --> 00:27:41,026
Chef Hyun-suk
is already off to a good start.

741
00:27:41,326 --> 00:27:43,061
THE FIRST FLASHY ATTACK

742
00:27:43,128 --> 00:27:44,896
-He looks relaxed.
-That took a while.

743
00:27:44,963 --> 00:27:45,997
Oyster sauce? What?

744
00:27:46,064 --> 00:27:48,733
-You're using that much? What?
-Isn't that too much?

745
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:52,037
-Really?
-He's measuring it.

746
00:27:52,103 --> 00:27:53,938
He can no longer eyeball the ingredients.

747
00:27:54,005 --> 00:27:56,941
-It's for the sauce for the eel.
-He's making exact measurements.

748
00:27:57,008 --> 00:27:58,376
He seems relaxed.

749
00:27:58,443 --> 00:28:01,246
Up against him is Chef Sam.
What's he up to?

750
00:28:01,312 --> 00:28:03,248
ONION, GREEN ONION, GARLIC

751
00:28:03,415 --> 00:28:04,616
DOENJANG

752
00:28:04,949 --> 00:28:07,318
SOY SAUCE & SUGAR

753
00:28:07,519 --> 00:28:08,586
PORK FOR BOILING

754
00:28:08,653 --> 00:28:11,723
-That's pork for boiling, to make <i>suyuk</i>.
-Yes, for <i>suyuk</i>.

755
00:28:11,790 --> 00:28:14,025
-Jin-young loves <i>suyuk</i>.
-It looks good.

756
00:28:14,092 --> 00:28:17,128
-He needs to move quickly. 13 minutes.
-Yes, <i>suyuk</i> takes a while.

757
00:28:17,195 --> 00:28:18,363
The time.

758
00:28:18,430 --> 00:28:20,465
-The lid.
-Will he steam it?

759
00:28:20,532 --> 00:28:21,766
Can he make that in 15 minutes?

760
00:28:21,833 --> 00:28:23,134
WILL IT COOK FULLY IN TIME?

761
00:28:23,368 --> 00:28:24,602
HYUN-SUK SAID HE'D MAKE EEL

762
00:28:24,669 --> 00:28:26,237
Wait, that's not an eel.

763
00:28:26,304 --> 00:28:29,140
He's not using eels, but beef.

764
00:28:29,207 --> 00:28:30,375
Rib meat?

765
00:28:31,076 --> 00:28:33,078
CUTTING

766
00:28:33,144 --> 00:28:34,913
Is he making it into an eel shape?

767
00:28:36,881 --> 00:28:38,817
It looks like the tail.

768
00:28:39,017 --> 00:28:41,219
I SEE

769
00:28:41,286 --> 00:28:44,389
-He's shaping it like an eel.
-The eel…

770
00:28:44,456 --> 00:28:47,325
-You should change its color too.
-How can that taste like an eel

771
00:28:47,392 --> 00:28:49,394
unless someone is an idiot?

772
00:28:49,461 --> 00:28:51,763
It obviously looks like
a long-shaped beef.

773
00:28:51,830 --> 00:28:54,432
-It's just beef over rice.
-It is.

774
00:28:54,499 --> 00:28:56,301
-It better look like an eel.
-Right?

775
00:28:56,634 --> 00:28:58,436
DESTROYING SUSPICION BY HAMMERING!

776
00:28:59,003 --> 00:29:01,840
I wonder what he'll do
after flattening the meat.

777
00:29:01,906 --> 00:29:06,277
-He's doing something in the center.
-He's shaping the meat.

778
00:29:06,344 --> 00:29:07,779
To make it look like an eel.

779
00:29:07,846 --> 00:29:09,114
That's such a petty trick.

780
00:29:09,180 --> 00:29:11,116
-Right?
-It's beef over rice.

781
00:29:11,182 --> 00:29:13,184
-You can't fool us that easily.
-No.

782
00:29:13,251 --> 00:29:16,121
-It looks like an eel.
-It has the shape.

783
00:29:16,187 --> 00:29:19,257
-It looks like eel.
-It has the shape.

784
00:29:19,324 --> 00:29:21,326
It does look like eel.

785
00:29:21,392 --> 00:29:23,094
It really does.

786
00:29:23,461 --> 00:29:24,462
QUITE SIMILAR

787
00:29:24,529 --> 00:29:25,530
He got the shape right.

788
00:29:25,597 --> 00:29:27,866
Hyun-suk takes
everyone's attention for now.

789
00:29:27,932 --> 00:29:28,933
That's what he's doing.

790
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:30,268
HE GOT EVERYONE'S ATTENTION, AT LEAST

791
00:29:30,335 --> 00:29:31,936
He's using skewers.

792
00:29:32,570 --> 00:29:34,205
The skewers…

793
00:29:34,272 --> 00:29:36,808
That's how you put skewers into an eel.

794
00:29:37,208 --> 00:29:39,244
COVERING WITH STARCH

795
00:29:39,511 --> 00:29:40,612
THIS ROUND IS ABOUT FLASHINESS,

796
00:29:40,845 --> 00:29:42,213
SO I'LL MAKE IT HAPPEN!

797
00:29:42,647 --> 00:29:43,848
He puts on a show!

798
00:29:43,915 --> 00:29:45,183
HI-YAH!

799
00:29:46,050 --> 00:29:47,051
He puts on a show!

800
00:29:47,118 --> 00:29:48,553
THAT'S WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT

801
00:29:48,620 --> 00:29:50,488
Look at his flashy performance!

802
00:29:50,555 --> 00:29:52,657
-He's flashy!
-That was so flashy.

803
00:29:52,724 --> 00:29:54,793
Look at his flashy performance!

804
00:29:54,859 --> 00:29:56,194
Is that flour?

805
00:29:56,261 --> 00:29:58,763
-Did he coat it with flour?
-Is he parboiling it?

806
00:29:58,830 --> 00:30:01,099
Once you put it in water,
it'll coat the meat

807
00:30:01,166 --> 00:30:02,867
and make the surface slippery.

808
00:30:02,934 --> 00:30:06,604
Yes, I'm adding
the slippery texture of an eel.

809
00:30:06,671 --> 00:30:08,673
-It's how you cook an eel.
-And making it tender.

810
00:30:08,740 --> 00:30:11,442
Shouldn't you get started on rice?
You're using a hot stone pot.

811
00:30:11,509 --> 00:30:12,644
I'll do it right now.

812
00:30:12,877 --> 00:30:14,579
SESAME OIL, MINCED GARLIC

813
00:30:15,814 --> 00:30:19,584
That's the beef his mother sent to him
as soon as it was butchered.

814
00:30:19,651 --> 00:30:21,186
+SALT
LAYERED ON BOTTOM!

815
00:30:21,586 --> 00:30:23,988
CHOP GREEN ONION AND THROW THAT IN TOO!

816
00:30:24,055 --> 00:30:26,090
He's stir-frying meat and green onion.

817
00:30:26,524 --> 00:30:28,226
ADDING SOAKED RICE

818
00:30:28,293 --> 00:30:31,429
-That's rice.
-I just put the rice in.

819
00:30:31,496 --> 00:30:34,465
-I hope the rice gets ready in time.
-Me too.

820
00:30:34,532 --> 00:30:37,569
-You have 11 minutes left.
-Time flies.

821
00:30:37,635 --> 00:30:39,704
The time. My gosh.

822
00:30:40,338 --> 00:30:44,008
-He's coating it with the sauce.
-Eel sauce, then straight to the flame.

823
00:30:44,075 --> 00:30:45,210
HE'LL GRILL IT OVER CHARCOAL

824
00:30:45,276 --> 00:30:46,945
That's nice. Great idea.

825
00:30:47,011 --> 00:30:50,315
He's doing his best
to make it look like an eel.

826
00:30:50,381 --> 00:30:51,716
GRILLED JUST LIKE AN EEL!

827
00:30:51,783 --> 00:30:53,751
That rib meat looks good, though.

828
00:30:53,818 --> 00:30:55,753
-It looks similar to grilled pork neck.
-Right?

829
00:30:56,221 --> 00:30:59,357
FAN MASTER CHOI IS HERE

830
00:30:59,424 --> 00:31:02,694
-There it is. There's the fan.
-He grabs the fan.

831
00:31:03,127 --> 00:31:04,362
FLAP FLAP

832
00:31:04,729 --> 00:31:07,131
THE FAN MASTER OF CCW2
LOOKED MORE LIKE THIS

833
00:31:07,198 --> 00:31:09,167
Look at Hyun-suk's flashy performance!

834
00:31:09,234 --> 00:31:10,969
He's dominating the round!

835
00:31:11,035 --> 00:31:12,637
THE WORLD OF MUSIC HAS THE FAN DANCE

836
00:31:13,071 --> 00:31:16,241
AND THE WORLD OF CULINARY ARTS
HAS THIS MAN!

837
00:31:16,641 --> 00:31:18,243
THE GRANDPA'S FAN DANCE!

838
00:31:18,810 --> 00:31:20,511
We've forgotten all about Sam.

839
00:31:20,578 --> 00:31:22,213
SAM? MOVE ASIDE!

840
00:31:22,714 --> 00:31:24,449
AS STRONG AS A TORNADO!

841
00:31:24,515 --> 00:31:26,751
-The charcoal is flying everywhere.
-It's not supposed to do that.

842
00:31:27,752 --> 00:31:30,555
He's doing his best
to make it look like an eel.

843
00:31:30,622 --> 00:31:32,523
It's an eel grilled over charcoal.

844
00:31:32,590 --> 00:31:34,192
Isn't the fire too big?

845
00:31:34,259 --> 00:31:35,526
Yes, it's too big.

846
00:31:35,793 --> 00:31:37,528
BURNING

847
00:31:38,363 --> 00:31:40,899
-It's burnt!
-It's burnt!

848
00:31:40,965 --> 00:31:42,867
-It's an emergency. Where is it?
-Ring the alarm.

849
00:31:42,934 --> 00:31:45,370
-It looks quite burnt.
-No! It's an emergency!

850
00:31:45,436 --> 00:31:47,105
No, Master Choi.

851
00:31:47,171 --> 00:31:49,140
So far, it's just grilled meat.

852
00:31:49,207 --> 00:31:51,776
-It's just grilled ribs.
-That's not an eel.

853
00:31:51,843 --> 00:31:53,544
-The rib's burnt.
-It's burnt.

854
00:31:53,611 --> 00:31:55,113
Will you just insist that it's an eel?

855
00:31:55,747 --> 00:31:57,515
EVERYONE CONDEMNS THE EMPTY VESSEL

856
00:31:57,582 --> 00:31:58,917
"Will you just insist?"

857
00:31:58,983 --> 00:32:00,952
-Is he trying to make it darker?
-Is he?

858
00:32:01,019 --> 00:32:03,288
He's burning the meat to make it darker?

859
00:32:03,354 --> 00:32:05,056
Just like how eel skin looks?

860
00:32:05,123 --> 00:32:06,557
-I see.
-Completely charred?

861
00:32:06,624 --> 00:32:08,159
-Is that so?
-Is that so?

862
00:32:08,226 --> 00:32:11,029
But it'll be too charred
if he does that with beef.

863
00:32:11,229 --> 00:32:12,430
ONE MORE DIP INTO THE SAUCE

864
00:32:12,497 --> 00:32:14,499
-He's dipping it in the sauce.
-One more time.

865
00:32:14,565 --> 00:32:15,700
Back over the fire.

866
00:32:15,767 --> 00:32:18,670
I can smell it from here,
and it's like Japanese-style grilled beef.

867
00:32:19,604 --> 00:32:21,806
That means he's just making beef.

868
00:32:21,873 --> 00:32:22,874
STILL INSISTS ON FANNING

869
00:32:22,941 --> 00:32:24,075
I want to take a video of this.

870
00:32:24,375 --> 00:32:26,210
FANNING

871
00:32:26,477 --> 00:32:28,680
WHEN WILL IT TURN INTO AN EEL?

872
00:32:29,113 --> 00:32:30,848
SAM LOST HIS TIME ON AIR
BECAUSE OF HIS NEIGHBOR

873
00:32:31,149 --> 00:32:35,887
1. STIR-FRY STRIP LOIN, GARLIC,
OYSTER SAUCE, SALT, AND PEPPER

874
00:32:35,954 --> 00:32:39,157
AS THE TOPPING FOR THE HOT STONE POT RICE

875
00:32:39,223 --> 00:32:40,591
It smells so good.

876
00:32:40,658 --> 00:32:44,228
It would be great
if Sam could put on a flashy show too.

877
00:32:44,796 --> 00:32:45,930
Not yet.

878
00:32:46,531 --> 00:32:49,133
HE CONTINUES TO PREP INGREDIENTS QUIETLY!

879
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:50,568
2. MIX DIFFERENT SPICES

880
00:32:50,635 --> 00:32:53,371
Chopped garlic, onion,
vinegar, and olive oil.

881
00:32:53,438 --> 00:32:55,406
-Is that cilantro?
-It is.

882
00:32:55,473 --> 00:32:57,809
-I think he's making chimichurri.
-Chimichurri?

883
00:32:57,875 --> 00:32:59,210
OLIVE OIL, SOY SAUCE

884
00:32:59,277 --> 00:33:00,778
Chimichurri.

885
00:33:00,845 --> 00:33:02,413
It's often served with meat

886
00:33:02,480 --> 00:33:04,349
-in South America.
-That sauce?

887
00:33:04,415 --> 00:33:05,750
They have eight minutes left.

888
00:33:05,817 --> 00:33:07,385
It's going to be me next.

889
00:33:07,952 --> 00:33:09,320
-You're up next.
-What about the rice?

890
00:33:09,587 --> 00:33:11,356
CHOPPED ONION

891
00:33:11,622 --> 00:33:13,758
3. STIR-FRY CHOPPED ONION WITH THE SAUCE

892
00:33:14,926 --> 00:33:16,594
A FLASHY FIRE SHOW

893
00:33:16,661 --> 00:33:19,330
-He's cooking onions.
-He seizes the lead with a fire show.

894
00:33:19,831 --> 00:33:20,832
PRETENDING TO HAVE SHORT LIMBS

895
00:33:22,100 --> 00:33:23,634
AN HOMAGE TO THE SHORT-LIMBED BIG GUY

896
00:33:23,901 --> 00:33:24,936
THE FLASHY GRANDPA IS BUSY

897
00:33:25,503 --> 00:33:27,905
-He's been copying me often lately.
-That's <i>mantecare</i>.

898
00:33:27,972 --> 00:33:30,074
He gets cold easily too.

899
00:33:30,375 --> 00:33:32,543
THAT'S WHY HE'S SETTING THINGS ON FIRE

900
00:33:32,844 --> 00:33:34,445
WHILE HE'S SHOWING FLASHY MOVES…

901
00:33:34,512 --> 00:33:35,646
Your meat!

902
00:33:35,713 --> 00:33:37,015
It's burning!

903
00:33:37,515 --> 00:33:38,750
BURNING

904
00:33:39,183 --> 00:33:40,518
HUH?

905
00:33:40,818 --> 00:33:42,120
IT'S AN EMERGENCY

906
00:33:42,186 --> 00:33:43,621
-It's burning!
-The meat!

907
00:33:43,688 --> 00:33:45,323
-No!
-The meat!

908
00:33:45,623 --> 00:33:47,258
EVERYONE GROANS

909
00:33:47,325 --> 00:33:48,359
It's ruined!

910
00:33:48,426 --> 00:33:49,427
NOPE

911
00:33:49,494 --> 00:33:51,729
Hyun-suk! It looks seriously burnt!

912
00:33:51,796 --> 00:33:52,797
BLACKENED RIB MEAT

913
00:33:52,864 --> 00:33:54,132
Look at that!

914
00:33:54,966 --> 00:33:56,667
It's an emergency!

915
00:33:56,734 --> 00:34:01,205
-No!
-He's resorting to cutting the burnt part.

916
00:34:01,272 --> 00:34:03,174
-Hyun-suk!
-It'll taste smoky.

917
00:34:03,241 --> 00:34:05,476
-It'll taste burnt.
-It'll taste like charcoal.

918
00:34:05,543 --> 00:34:06,778
-Burnt.
-It'll taste like charcoal?

919
00:34:06,844 --> 00:34:08,379
It's a serious emergency.

920
00:34:08,446 --> 00:34:11,282
He keeps coating it with more sauce,

921
00:34:11,349 --> 00:34:13,284
which is making it more burnt.

922
00:34:13,351 --> 00:34:14,919
It looks like an eel, though.

923
00:34:14,986 --> 00:34:16,421
It looks good.

924
00:34:16,487 --> 00:34:17,989
Not really, but it does look like an eel.

925
00:34:18,056 --> 00:34:19,590
It doesn't look good?

926
00:34:19,657 --> 00:34:20,925
You have seven minutes left.

927
00:34:20,992 --> 00:34:22,593
Sam grabs some cabbage.

928
00:34:22,660 --> 00:34:25,329
Sam is busy prepping a lot of ingredients.

929
00:34:25,396 --> 00:34:26,764
3. JULIENNE CABBAGE

930
00:34:26,831 --> 00:34:28,366
Isn't that what we call flashy?

931
00:34:29,067 --> 00:34:30,134
NATURALIST FLASHINESS

932
00:34:30,201 --> 00:34:31,669
-That's flashy.
-The flashy cutting skills.

933
00:34:32,036 --> 00:34:33,905
THE CABBAGE IS AS THIN AS A THREAD

934
00:34:33,971 --> 00:34:35,940
-Butterhead lettuce?
-Butterhead.

935
00:34:36,007 --> 00:34:38,709
Sam uses lots of vegetables.

936
00:34:38,776 --> 00:34:40,711
-Is that cilantro for the rice?
-That's a lot of veggies.

937
00:34:40,778 --> 00:34:41,779
Yes, it is.

938
00:34:42,413 --> 00:34:44,449
He came ready today.

939
00:34:44,682 --> 00:34:46,451
WHAT WILL HYUN-SUK DO NEXT?

940
00:34:46,517 --> 00:34:47,685
He's making the soup now.

941
00:34:47,752 --> 00:34:50,354
-You get a minute for the soup.
-Here we go.

942
00:34:50,721 --> 00:34:51,722
BONITO POWDER

943
00:34:52,390 --> 00:34:53,691
It better be ready

944
00:34:53,758 --> 00:34:55,526
when the clock hits
5 minutes and 20 seconds.

945
00:34:55,793 --> 00:34:58,396
DISSOLVE DOENJANG IN WATER

946
00:34:59,230 --> 00:35:02,266
AND MIX WITH AN IMMERSION BLENDER

947
00:35:02,333 --> 00:35:05,303
He said he'd make the soup
in just a minute.

948
00:35:05,970 --> 00:35:08,106
-Oh, no.
-Just do it for now.

949
00:35:08,172 --> 00:35:09,207
What is it?

950
00:35:09,273 --> 00:35:12,076
No, not there. Don't pour it there.

951
00:35:12,143 --> 00:35:15,446
He's straining the soybeans.

952
00:35:15,513 --> 00:35:18,116
-He strains the mixture.
-To get rid of the extra smell.

953
00:35:18,182 --> 00:35:19,417
-And boil it?
-You're boiling it?

954
00:35:19,484 --> 00:35:20,918
4. MIX BROTH WITH THE DOENJANG MIXTURE

955
00:35:20,985 --> 00:35:23,154
-That's it?
-That's it?

956
00:35:23,855 --> 00:35:24,922
There's something else.

957
00:35:24,989 --> 00:35:26,858
-I'm sure there is.
-He's doing something. No?

958
00:35:26,924 --> 00:35:29,694
It better be ready
in 20 seconds, Chef Hyun-suk.

959
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:31,529
You have 20 seconds left.

960
00:35:31,596 --> 00:35:32,930
It's not boiling.

961
00:35:32,997 --> 00:35:34,031
IT NEEDS SALT!

962
00:35:34,098 --> 00:35:35,399
It's not boiling.

963
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:38,369
I WON'T MISS A CHANCE TO BE FLASHY

964
00:35:39,837 --> 00:35:40,838
ONE MORE TIME!

965
00:35:41,272 --> 00:35:43,441
FLASHY WITH BOTH HANDS!

966
00:35:43,508 --> 00:35:44,809
-Come on.
-That didn't go in.

967
00:35:44,876 --> 00:35:46,010
Is it ready?

968
00:35:46,077 --> 00:35:47,311
-It is.
-It is.

969
00:35:47,378 --> 00:35:49,180
-It's ready?
-It hasn't boiled.

970
00:35:49,247 --> 00:35:50,648
It's a cold soup.

971
00:35:50,848 --> 00:35:52,483
CILANTRO

972
00:35:52,550 --> 00:35:53,551
IT'S NOT A COLD SOUP!

973
00:35:54,252 --> 00:35:55,253
A LONG-DISTANCE ATTACK!

974
00:35:55,586 --> 00:35:57,054
FLOUNDERING

975
00:35:57,455 --> 00:35:59,290
HE'S ALL OVER THE PLACE TODAY

976
00:35:59,357 --> 00:36:01,726
He just shook the water off
from the cilantro

977
00:36:01,792 --> 00:36:03,928
-while facing Sam.
-It's a cold soup.

978
00:36:04,195 --> 00:36:05,196
THE SOUP

979
00:36:05,263 --> 00:36:06,264
5. MAKE CILANTRO SALAD

980
00:36:06,330 --> 00:36:08,799
-Balsamic vinegar?
-Balsamic vinegar and olive oil.

981
00:36:10,001 --> 00:36:11,502
He's going to shake Sam down.

982
00:36:11,569 --> 00:36:14,005
-Sung-ju, can you report from the kitchen?
-Yes?

983
00:36:14,071 --> 00:36:15,840
Will you come with me, Yu-jin?

984
00:36:15,907 --> 00:36:17,475
-I'd love to.
-Yu-jin.

985
00:36:17,542 --> 00:36:19,677
Let us do the five-minute check.

986
00:36:21,913 --> 00:36:23,281
SAM CHECKS ON THE SUYUK

987
00:36:23,347 --> 00:36:25,383
-<i>Suyuk</i>.
-We're here to check.

988
00:36:25,449 --> 00:36:27,018
Has it been cooked well?

989
00:36:27,084 --> 00:36:29,520
-It still seems reddish.
-You should check and see.

990
00:36:29,587 --> 00:36:31,422
-Cut it.
-You cut it out with scissors earlier.

991
00:36:31,489 --> 00:36:32,490
I'm sure it's cooked.

992
00:36:32,757 --> 00:36:34,225
HE PULLED IT OUT ONLY AFTER 10 MINUTES

993
00:36:34,292 --> 00:36:35,826
Do you think so? I doubt it.

994
00:36:35,893 --> 00:36:37,528
-No?
-I doubt it's fully cooked.

995
00:36:37,595 --> 00:36:39,030
Let me try the soup!

996
00:36:39,096 --> 00:36:40,331
Oh, no!

997
00:36:40,398 --> 00:36:41,399
It's still raw!

998
00:36:41,465 --> 00:36:43,100
Oh, no!

999
00:36:43,167 --> 00:36:45,102
-It's still raw!
-It's red!

1000
00:36:45,169 --> 00:36:48,539
His <i>suyuk </i>isn't fully cooked!

1001
00:36:48,606 --> 00:36:50,408
-No! It's raw!
-No, it's okay.

1002
00:36:50,474 --> 00:36:53,711
-It's not cooked!
-It needs more heat.

1003
00:36:53,778 --> 00:36:55,346
You can't cook it in there. Just grill it!

1004
00:36:55,413 --> 00:36:58,049
Grill it over that charcoal over there!

1005
00:36:58,115 --> 00:37:00,785
Just cook it over charcoal!
That'll be much better!

1006
00:37:00,851 --> 00:37:02,186
It won't be <i>suyuk</i> anymore.

1007
00:37:02,253 --> 00:37:05,156
-It'll be fine! Just grill it!
-As long as it's good.

1008
00:37:05,723 --> 00:37:07,558
MEDIUM-RARE SUYUK

1009
00:37:07,625 --> 00:37:09,060
Just put it in!

1010
00:37:09,126 --> 00:37:12,730
That's a much better bet
than serving it raw! Right now!

1011
00:37:12,797 --> 00:37:14,765
IT MUST BE SHOCKING, YU-JIN

1012
00:37:14,832 --> 00:37:16,634
-I'll cook it in here.
-What?

1013
00:37:16,701 --> 00:37:18,502
-It's hot.
-It's hot?

1014
00:37:18,569 --> 00:37:21,239
-I can cook it in the pot.
-But the heat is off. Is that okay?

1015
00:37:21,305 --> 00:37:24,275
-It's okay.
-The heat is off. It's an emergency.

1016
00:37:24,342 --> 00:37:26,777
-Turn the heat on.
-Just grill it over charcoal.

1017
00:37:26,844 --> 00:37:29,547
-No, please turn the heat on.
-Chef Kim can do this.

1018
00:37:29,614 --> 00:37:31,682
At least turn the heat on.
It's an emergency!

1019
00:37:31,749 --> 00:37:33,150
Try the soup.

1020
00:37:33,217 --> 00:37:36,621
Hyun-suk made this soup
in just one minute.

1021
00:37:36,687 --> 00:37:39,357
Does it taste flashy?

1022
00:37:41,492 --> 00:37:44,662
THE CLOSEST SHOT IN HISTORY

1023
00:37:44,729 --> 00:37:46,897
She put it right in front of his mouth.

1024
00:37:47,164 --> 00:37:48,866
FISH-EYE LENS

1025
00:37:48,933 --> 00:37:50,768
-It's a little bland.
-Is it?

1026
00:37:50,835 --> 00:37:52,370
-It's bland?
-It's bland.

1027
00:37:52,436 --> 00:37:54,639
-It hasn't boiled yet.
-It needs more salt.

1028
00:37:54,705 --> 00:37:56,307
The salt he threw missed the pot.

1029
00:37:56,374 --> 00:37:58,709
-It needs more salt.
-It's a little bland.

1030
00:37:58,776 --> 00:38:01,112
All right.
You can take the camera, Yu-jin.

1031
00:38:01,746 --> 00:38:03,581
SAM ALREADY BEGINS PLATING THE FOOD!

1032
00:38:03,648 --> 00:38:04,649
CHIMICHURRI SAUCE

1033
00:38:05,049 --> 00:38:08,619
TOPPED WITH JULIENNED CABBAGE

1034
00:38:09,353 --> 00:38:11,522
Is the heat on? It's not on!

1035
00:38:11,589 --> 00:38:13,124
-No, it's fine.
-Cook it some more!

1036
00:38:13,190 --> 00:38:15,693
It's all right even if it isn't <i>suyuk</i>.
Just grill that meat!

1037
00:38:15,760 --> 00:38:18,329
Come on, man!
How are you going to serve that?

1038
00:38:19,363 --> 00:38:22,199
The pork hasn't been cooked fully.

1039
00:38:23,167 --> 00:38:24,735
It's getting cooked.

1040
00:38:25,303 --> 00:38:26,771
The heat isn't on.

1041
00:38:26,837 --> 00:38:28,739
-You don't need to turn it on?
-But he says it's fine.

1042
00:38:28,806 --> 00:38:30,741
-I don't need to turn it on.
-You don't?

1043
00:38:30,808 --> 00:38:32,543
HE CONTINUES WITHOUT TURNING THE HEAT ON

1044
00:38:32,610 --> 00:38:35,379
Turn the heat on!
Please cook it thoroughly!

1045
00:38:35,446 --> 00:38:37,648
-Put it over the charcoal!
-He might die soon.

1046
00:38:38,215 --> 00:38:39,684
You have to cook it, though.

1047
00:38:39,750 --> 00:38:41,919
-Put it over the charcoal!
-You have to cook it, though.

1048
00:38:41,986 --> 00:38:43,287
It's cooked.

1049
00:38:43,354 --> 00:38:45,756
You have to cook it completely! Come on.

1050
00:38:45,823 --> 00:38:47,658
-It's cooked. Look.
-What's he going to do?

1051
00:38:47,725 --> 00:38:49,493
Put a piece down and let us try it.

1052
00:38:49,560 --> 00:38:52,163
-You can't. I have to use it.
-You have to use it?

1053
00:38:52,229 --> 00:38:54,799
We can't even try it.
He'll serve it just like that.

1054
00:38:54,865 --> 00:38:56,634
-He's a bit sensitive.
-He is.

1055
00:38:56,701 --> 00:38:59,503
Sam is a bit sensitive right now.
We should steer clear.

1056
00:38:59,570 --> 00:39:00,971
He doesn't have too many pieces.

1057
00:39:01,739 --> 00:39:03,407
TOPPING WITH CHIMICHURRI

1058
00:39:03,708 --> 00:39:04,775
WHAT'S HYUN-SUK DOING NOW?

1059
00:39:05,142 --> 00:39:08,679
PLATING HEATED RICE

1060
00:39:08,846 --> 00:39:11,582
SOY-BASED SAUCE, STIR-FRIED ONION,
CILANTRO SALAD

1061
00:39:11,749 --> 00:39:12,883
ALL HE NEEDS ARE THE RIBS

1062
00:39:14,051 --> 00:39:15,986
It does look like eel.

1063
00:39:16,053 --> 00:39:18,489
-It looks similar to eel.
-He's plating the food.

1064
00:39:18,556 --> 00:39:21,392
-It really looks like eel.
-It really does.

1065
00:39:21,459 --> 00:39:23,327
If you squint, it looks like eel.

1066
00:39:23,861 --> 00:39:25,029
SQUINTING

1067
00:39:25,096 --> 00:39:26,097
Then it looks like eel.

1068
00:39:26,163 --> 00:39:27,164
LIKE THIS!

1069
00:39:27,231 --> 00:39:28,499
Look at it with one eye.

1070
00:39:28,566 --> 00:39:30,935
-You must squint as you look at it.
-It looks like eel.

1071
00:39:31,001 --> 00:39:33,471
It looks like eel
when you look at it like this.

1072
00:39:33,537 --> 00:39:36,741
-It looks like it when I squint.
-If you squint, it looks like eel.

1073
00:39:37,041 --> 00:39:38,776
THE CHERRY ON TOP, EGG YOLK

1074
00:39:38,843 --> 00:39:41,178
-It smells so good.
-He tops it with an egg yolk.

1075
00:39:41,245 --> 00:39:42,546
It looks delicious.

1076
00:39:42,613 --> 00:39:44,482
You have a minute and 54 seconds.

1077
00:39:44,548 --> 00:39:46,450
Everything is almost finished.

1078
00:39:46,717 --> 00:39:48,619
4. TOP RICE WITH THE TOPPING,
CILANTRO, SESAME OIL

1079
00:39:48,686 --> 00:39:51,088
The hot stone pot rice looks so good.

1080
00:39:51,155 --> 00:39:52,690
It looks nice.

1081
00:39:52,757 --> 00:39:55,659
The key is if this meat is cooked or not.

1082
00:39:55,726 --> 00:39:57,361
-It's cooked.
-I see.

1083
00:39:57,661 --> 00:39:58,662
HYUN-SUK WRAPS UP

1084
00:39:58,963 --> 00:40:03,367
6. ADD CHICKEN BREAST AND GREEN ONION
TO THE SOUP AND FINISH

1085
00:40:03,434 --> 00:40:04,502
THE SOUP IS READY TOO!

1086
00:40:04,568 --> 00:40:05,770
-Yu-jin.
-Yes?

1087
00:40:05,836 --> 00:40:07,405
Can you taste the eel sauce?

1088
00:40:07,471 --> 00:40:09,640
The eel sauce. Hyun-suk is done.

1089
00:40:09,707 --> 00:40:11,976
The eel sauce.

1090
00:40:12,042 --> 00:40:13,277
It smells rather salty.

1091
00:40:13,344 --> 00:40:14,578
IT'LL BE HER VERY FIRST REVIEW

1092
00:40:14,645 --> 00:40:17,248
Does it taste flashy or trashy?

1093
00:40:17,581 --> 00:40:20,050
WHAT DOES YU-JIN THINK?

1094
00:40:20,117 --> 00:40:21,886
Man, it's so flashy!

1095
00:40:22,820 --> 00:40:23,821
A BIG SMILE

1096
00:40:23,888 --> 00:40:25,556
It's so flashy!

1097
00:40:25,823 --> 00:40:27,391
AN ENCORE FOR HER CUTENESS

1098
00:40:27,892 --> 00:40:29,326
THAT'S WHY SHE'S A K-POP IDOL

1099
00:40:29,393 --> 00:40:31,061
It's so flashy!

1100
00:40:31,128 --> 00:40:33,831
-It's not trashy.
-It's so good!

1101
00:40:34,231 --> 00:40:35,433
SAM BEGINS TO WRAP UP TOO

1102
00:40:35,800 --> 00:40:36,967
TOPPING SUYUK SAUCE WITH CILANTRO

1103
00:40:37,034 --> 00:40:39,069
-He really uses a lot of cilantro.
-Wouldn't it be too salty?

1104
00:40:39,136 --> 00:40:41,872
It's all right! And Sam is also done.

1105
00:40:41,939 --> 00:40:44,108
Sam finishes with 21 seconds left.

1106
00:40:44,809 --> 00:40:47,611
YU-JIN'S SHIFT IS OVER TOO

1107
00:40:48,179 --> 00:40:50,314
THE FAN GRANDPA IS AT IT AGAIN

1108
00:40:51,982 --> 00:40:54,885
THE FLASHY DISHES TAKE OFF

1109
00:40:56,187 --> 00:40:57,521
Is it made with pork hock?

1110
00:40:57,588 --> 00:41:02,026
And now, two flashy dishes were made
just for Jin-young.

1111
00:41:02,092 --> 00:41:03,427
THANK YOU

1112
00:41:03,694 --> 00:41:05,696
CLAPPING

1113
00:41:05,763 --> 00:41:09,366
Chef Hyun-suk finished making
Fan Master Choi first.

1114
00:41:09,433 --> 00:41:13,437
SOUP MADE IN 1 MINUTE
AND EEL OVER RICE WITHOUT AN EEL

1115
00:41:14,405 --> 00:41:17,808
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S FAN MASTER CHOI

1116
00:41:17,875 --> 00:41:20,110
It smells like a <i>galbi</i> place in Pocheon.

1117
00:41:20,177 --> 00:41:21,312
Grilled short ribs.

1118
00:41:21,378 --> 00:41:23,547
-Thank you.
-Soup always goes to your right.

1119
00:41:23,614 --> 00:41:26,917
Jin-young kept mentioning eel over rice,

1120
00:41:26,984 --> 00:41:29,286
as well as beef over rice.

1121
00:41:29,353 --> 00:41:31,655
<i>Onions aren't used</i>
<i>when you put eel over rice,</i>

1122
00:41:31,722 --> 00:41:33,891
<i>but they are for beef over rice.</i>

1123
00:41:33,958 --> 00:41:36,160
Also, it's not made with cilantro,

1124
00:41:36,227 --> 00:41:38,295
but it goes very well with soy sauce.

1125
00:41:38,863 --> 00:41:42,266
The ingredients you love
work very well together,

1126
00:41:42,333 --> 00:41:44,702
and I wanted to serve it to you
in the form of eel over rice.

1127
00:41:45,669 --> 00:41:46,670
Thank you.

1128
00:41:46,737 --> 00:41:48,506
Why did you cut the meat?

1129
00:41:48,572 --> 00:41:50,875
Eels are served in pieces too.

1130
00:41:50,941 --> 00:41:52,109
He tries the soup first.

1131
00:41:52,176 --> 00:41:54,278
It's the soup he made in a minute.

1132
00:41:54,912 --> 00:41:57,348
-You said it was a little bland.
-It was.

1133
00:41:57,414 --> 00:41:59,216
-Just a little.
-A little, right?

1134
00:41:59,283 --> 00:42:00,551
Do you like it?

1135
00:42:01,986 --> 00:42:03,521
I don't like overly salty food,

1136
00:42:04,622 --> 00:42:06,390
so it's perfect for my taste.

1137
00:42:06,457 --> 00:42:08,392
-I can't believe this.
-He was right on.

1138
00:42:08,459 --> 00:42:09,960
-He was right.
-I knew it.

1139
00:42:10,027 --> 00:42:11,028
FAN MASTER CHOI WAS SPOT ON

1140
00:42:11,095 --> 00:42:13,464
Also, the <i>doenjang</i> our family makes

1141
00:42:13,531 --> 00:42:14,565
is stronger than most.

1142
00:42:14,632 --> 00:42:18,302
So I found it amazing
that he turned it into this light flavor.

1143
00:42:18,369 --> 00:42:20,271
It's like miso soup.

1144
00:42:20,337 --> 00:42:22,239
How did he do that in a minute?

1145
00:42:22,306 --> 00:42:25,809
<i>Add bonito powder lightly into water.</i>

1146
00:42:25,876 --> 00:42:29,313
<i>Then add just a tiny bit of doenjang water</i>
<i>after blending it finely.</i>

1147
00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:32,449
-It tastes like Japanese soup.
-It's like Japanese soup.

1148
00:42:32,516 --> 00:42:34,652
BREAKING THE YOLK FIRST

1149
00:42:34,718 --> 00:42:36,186
Time to try the eel.

1150
00:42:36,754 --> 00:42:38,355
It obviously looks like beef.

1151
00:42:38,422 --> 00:42:40,724
-It does.
-But I love

1152
00:42:40,791 --> 00:42:44,194
how he vigorously insists
that what he made is eel.

1153
00:42:44,261 --> 00:42:46,664
-Right.
-It's obviously beef, right?

1154
00:42:46,730 --> 00:42:48,098
He took a bite.

1155
00:42:49,166 --> 00:42:50,801
He called it eel,

1156
00:42:50,868 --> 00:42:52,570
but you had a piece of beef.

1157
00:42:52,636 --> 00:42:56,307
But the sauce was the one for eel,
so I hope it has that flavor.

1158
00:42:56,373 --> 00:42:57,374
It's so good,

1159
00:42:57,441 --> 00:43:00,377
but it's definitely beef.

1160
00:43:00,444 --> 00:43:01,779
CALMLY THROWS A TRUTH BOMB

1161
00:43:01,845 --> 00:43:03,547
He's honest.

1162
00:43:03,614 --> 00:43:05,049
-It's delicious beef.
-It's obvious.

1163
00:43:05,115 --> 00:43:07,418
It's obviously beef,
but he kept saying it was eel.

1164
00:43:07,484 --> 00:43:08,852
-I'm sorry.
-He can't lie.

1165
00:43:08,919 --> 00:43:10,854
It's eel over rice
that tastes like beef over rice.

1166
00:43:10,921 --> 00:43:13,390
Jin-young denied it,
but he keeps insisting.

1167
00:43:13,457 --> 00:43:16,260
-He begins to dig in.
-It must taste good.

1168
00:43:16,327 --> 00:43:17,328
It looks good though.

1169
00:43:17,394 --> 00:43:19,763
But he says it doesn't taste like eel.

1170
00:43:19,830 --> 00:43:20,831
It looks good.

1171
00:43:20,898 --> 00:43:23,067
-It can't be bad.
-At least it's shaped like eel.

1172
00:43:23,133 --> 00:43:25,002
-It's only the presentation.
-I guess so.

1173
00:43:25,069 --> 00:43:26,570
It probably tastes good.

1174
00:43:26,637 --> 00:43:29,073
-It has to be good.
-He takes a big bite.

1175
00:43:29,139 --> 00:43:30,140
Beef over rice.

1176
00:43:30,207 --> 00:43:32,376
-Does it go well with cilantro?
-My mouth is watering.

1177
00:43:32,443 --> 00:43:33,444
Let's get some after the shoot.

1178
00:43:33,510 --> 00:43:36,146
-I can't endure it.
-Cilantro is the key.

1179
00:43:37,448 --> 00:43:41,785
I've never had cilantro
with dishes that have this flavor,

1180
00:43:41,852 --> 00:43:45,856
and it hits you a moment later
after you taste the beef.

1181
00:43:45,923 --> 00:43:49,159
<i>At first, the beef seems a bit greasy,</i>
<i>but it's balanced out with cilantro,</i>

1182
00:43:49,226 --> 00:43:50,327
<i>making it lighter.</i>

1183
00:43:52,429 --> 00:43:54,198
-I think it would be good.
-Actually,

1184
00:43:54,264 --> 00:43:57,901
neither eel over rice
or beef over rice use cilantro.

1185
00:43:57,968 --> 00:44:00,504
But Jin-young, you like cilantro,

1186
00:44:00,571 --> 00:44:01,872
so thank you so much for that.

1187
00:44:03,307 --> 00:44:05,242
AN UNEXPECTED TWIST

1188
00:44:05,309 --> 00:44:07,077
What's with that development?

1189
00:44:07,144 --> 00:44:10,848
I wanted to use some cilantro,
so I was glad that he liked it.

1190
00:44:10,914 --> 00:44:12,249
TAKES HIS THANKS AND TAKES ANOTHER BITE

1191
00:44:12,316 --> 00:44:14,685
-He eats so well.
-He does.

1192
00:44:15,653 --> 00:44:17,054
DINING WITH HIS FACE IN THE DISH

1193
00:44:17,121 --> 00:44:18,756
Has he starved for a few days?

1194
00:44:19,623 --> 00:44:22,459
HE CONTINUES TO CHOW THE RICE DOWN

1195
00:44:22,526 --> 00:44:24,161
He makes it look so good.

1196
00:44:24,228 --> 00:44:27,231
-He does. It's like watching <i>mukbang</i>.
-I'm drooling so much.

1197
00:44:27,297 --> 00:44:29,500
-I want to steal it from him.
-Right?

1198
00:44:30,567 --> 00:44:31,568
WON'T MISS A GRAIN

1199
00:44:31,635 --> 00:44:33,203
Are you watching, Jin-young's mom?

1200
00:44:34,004 --> 00:44:37,107
I never thought someone could make
something like this with my fridge.

1201
00:44:37,174 --> 00:44:39,076
-It was unimaginable.
-I see.

1202
00:44:39,143 --> 00:44:40,978
So? Was it flashy enough?

1203
00:44:41,545 --> 00:44:43,147
It's amazing.

1204
00:44:43,213 --> 00:44:46,350
-It's amazing.
-It was amazing, Chef Hyun-suk.

1205
00:44:46,417 --> 00:44:48,986
Next, Chef Sam's dish.

1206
00:44:49,820 --> 00:44:51,288
<i>Stop, You've Won Enough Times.</i>

1207
00:44:51,355 --> 00:44:55,225
CHIMICHURRI AND SUYUK SALAD

1208
00:44:56,060 --> 00:44:58,462
SERVED WITH CILANTRO HOT STONE POT RICE

1209
00:44:59,296 --> 00:45:03,434
CHEF SAM KIM'S
STOP, YOU'VE WON ENOUGH TIMES

1210
00:45:03,500 --> 00:45:07,037
Try a piece of boiled pork
with the veggies underneath,

1211
00:45:07,104 --> 00:45:09,339
including the sauce at the bottom,
all at once.

1212
00:45:09,406 --> 00:45:13,811
There was much talk
of the meat being fully cooked or not,

1213
00:45:13,877 --> 00:45:16,613
making Chef Sam very sensitive.

1214
00:45:16,680 --> 00:45:19,583
It seemed cooked to him,
but no one agreed.

1215
00:45:19,650 --> 00:45:21,518
-With the veggies.
-Yes.

1216
00:45:21,585 --> 00:45:22,586
It has to be cooked.

1217
00:45:23,587 --> 00:45:24,588
IN A BITE

1218
00:45:24,655 --> 00:45:26,857
-He eats so well.
-He makes it look so good.

1219
00:45:27,891 --> 00:45:31,462
-I hope the pork is cooked.
-Is it?

1220
00:45:31,528 --> 00:45:33,297
It's been cooked so nicely.

1221
00:45:33,363 --> 00:45:35,399
SUYUK WAS BOILED PERFECTLY

1222
00:45:35,466 --> 00:45:37,267
-I apologize.
-I'm sorry.

1223
00:45:37,334 --> 00:45:39,236
-Apologize to him.
-I'm sorry.

1224
00:45:39,303 --> 00:45:41,672
-Sam was right.
-You were.

1225
00:45:41,739 --> 00:45:42,740
-Yes.
-So it was cooked.

1226
00:45:42,806 --> 00:45:47,244
You said chimichurri was a sauce
mostly had in Mexico.

1227
00:45:47,311 --> 00:45:50,581
At times, Mexican food
tastes quite strong,

1228
00:45:50,647 --> 00:45:55,252
<i>but this sauce is perfectly sour</i>
<i>even for an ordinary Korean person.</i>

1229
00:45:55,319 --> 00:45:58,021
The cilantro isn't too strong, either.

1230
00:45:59,256 --> 00:46:01,091
-It looks good.
-It must be refreshing.

1231
00:46:01,158 --> 00:46:02,993
Yes, it's cool and refreshing.

1232
00:46:03,761 --> 00:46:05,562
He must've made it refreshing
with the sauce.

1233
00:46:05,629 --> 00:46:07,931
-Yes, like when eating with kimchi.
-Right.

1234
00:46:07,998 --> 00:46:10,033
It balances out
the greasiness of the meat.

1235
00:46:10,667 --> 00:46:12,035
SMACKING LIPS

1236
00:46:12,369 --> 00:46:13,737
HE KEEPS CRAVING CHIMICHURRI SUYUK

1237
00:46:13,804 --> 00:46:14,805
He keeps eating more.

1238
00:46:14,872 --> 00:46:17,574
-Shouldn't he have the rice too?
-You can have the rice too.

1239
00:46:17,641 --> 00:46:19,309
There's cilantro in there too.

1240
00:46:19,376 --> 00:46:22,346
We have to get the footage
of the pot giving off steam.

1241
00:46:22,412 --> 00:46:23,947
-Can you open it?
-The stone pot rice.

1242
00:46:24,648 --> 00:46:26,917
OPENING THE STONE POT RICE

1243
00:46:27,551 --> 00:46:30,287
IT LOOKS INSANELY GOOD

1244
00:46:30,354 --> 00:46:31,989
That's to die for!

1245
00:46:32,055 --> 00:46:33,924
It smells so good!

1246
00:46:33,991 --> 00:46:36,727
It smelled like cilantro
as soon as he opened it.

1247
00:46:36,794 --> 00:46:39,429
-There's meat in here too.
-He used some meat. Is that beef?

1248
00:46:39,496 --> 00:46:40,931
-It is.
-That's beef.

1249
00:46:40,998 --> 00:46:43,367
-Does cilantro go well with rice?
-Try a bite.

1250
00:46:43,433 --> 00:46:44,802
-Should he mix it?
-Yes.

1251
00:46:44,868 --> 00:46:46,336
These three?

1252
00:46:46,970 --> 00:46:48,238
You can toss the rice.

1253
00:46:50,574 --> 00:46:52,509
It must be good. Gosh, I want it so bad.

1254
00:46:52,576 --> 00:46:54,745
SPRINGING UP AT THE SAME TIME

1255
00:46:54,945 --> 00:46:57,114
ME TOO

1256
00:46:57,181 --> 00:46:58,816
What's going on? Are you all meerkats?

1257
00:46:59,082 --> 00:47:00,984
BEWITCHED BY STONE POT RICE

1258
00:47:01,051 --> 00:47:02,419
-No one has seen this.
-No.

1259
00:47:02,486 --> 00:47:03,921
It smells amazing.

1260
00:47:04,254 --> 00:47:05,756
IN AWE

1261
00:47:05,823 --> 00:47:09,092
-That fresh rice must be so good.
-Look at the scorched rice.

1262
00:47:09,159 --> 00:47:12,129
-You just need a bit of sauce.
-Don't use too much sauce.

1263
00:47:12,196 --> 00:47:13,564
-While tasting it.
-It's seasoned already.

1264
00:47:13,630 --> 00:47:15,232
The topping was made with beef.

1265
00:47:15,299 --> 00:47:17,701
-It's like seasoned vegetables.
-I wonder what it's like.

1266
00:47:18,302 --> 00:47:19,803
-It looks good.
-He eats well.

1267
00:47:22,539 --> 00:47:24,241
SNIFFING THE AIR

1268
00:47:27,044 --> 00:47:28,045
More sauce?

1269
00:47:28,111 --> 00:47:30,647
-It isn't salty.
-He could use more sauce.

1270
00:47:30,714 --> 00:47:33,717
It's not salty at all.
I think I can use lots of sauce.

1271
00:47:34,985 --> 00:47:38,055
-It must taste very flashy.
-He can add sauce as he pleases.

1272
00:47:38,121 --> 00:47:39,690
He has a flashy way of eating.

1273
00:47:39,756 --> 00:47:41,558
-Right?
-Mmm.

1274
00:47:41,625 --> 00:47:42,926
I guess he needed lots of sauce.

1275
00:47:43,927 --> 00:47:45,429
-Gosh!
-My mouth is watering.

1276
00:47:45,495 --> 00:47:47,097
-What's the sauce?
-Meat sauce.

1277
00:47:47,164 --> 00:47:49,032
With the water he cooked the pork with.

1278
00:47:49,099 --> 00:47:52,569
<i>It's made by mixing</i>
doenjang <i>and pork broth.</i>

1279
00:47:52,636 --> 00:47:55,539
-It looks good.
-It's rich and nutty.

1280
00:47:56,440 --> 00:47:58,842
How's the cilantro smell working for you?

1281
00:47:58,909 --> 00:48:01,011
The whole rice smells like cilantro,

1282
00:48:01,078 --> 00:48:02,145
so it's not too strong.

1283
00:48:02,212 --> 00:48:05,282
-It lingers subtly in my mouth.
-So the smell remains.

1284
00:48:05,349 --> 00:48:06,917
-And you like cilantro.
-That looks so good.

1285
00:48:06,984 --> 00:48:08,852
-Also…
-I can't take this anymore.

1286
00:48:08,919 --> 00:48:11,922
…the pieces of meat were diced,

1287
00:48:11,989 --> 00:48:14,157
so it doesn't hurt my jaw.

1288
00:48:14,224 --> 00:48:17,227
Rice tastes delicious
with a dash of rich fat.

1289
00:48:17,294 --> 00:48:18,762
AMAZED AND FOCUSED ON EATING

1290
00:48:18,829 --> 00:48:21,265
He makes it look so delicious.

1291
00:48:21,331 --> 00:48:23,734
He would make a great <i>mukbang</i> creator.

1292
00:48:24,735 --> 00:48:27,271
THANK YOU FOR THE DISH

1293
00:48:27,337 --> 00:48:29,940
-Goodness.
-The way he enjoyed it says it all.

1294
00:48:30,007 --> 00:48:31,775
Let's try Chef Hyun-suk's dish first.

1295
00:48:31,842 --> 00:48:33,477
-Fan Master Choi.
-It's so pretty.

1296
00:48:33,543 --> 00:48:36,513
-No cilantro here. She doesn't like it.
-Yes, thank you.

1297
00:48:36,580 --> 00:48:38,215
May I give this to them?

1298
00:48:38,282 --> 00:48:39,583
Sure, but I ate out of it.

1299
00:48:40,150 --> 00:48:42,986
THE REMAINING EEL OVER RICE
GOES TO THE BIG TWINS

1300
00:48:43,053 --> 00:48:44,554
Another one? Okay!

1301
00:48:44,621 --> 00:48:46,657
Take the soup too.

1302
00:48:46,723 --> 00:48:48,558
Tell us what it's like.

1303
00:48:48,625 --> 00:48:49,693
They never waste any food.

1304
00:48:50,160 --> 00:48:52,029
YUM

1305
00:48:53,163 --> 00:48:54,665
YU-JIN TAKES A BITE TOO

1306
00:48:54,731 --> 00:48:56,266
They never waste any food.

1307
00:48:58,669 --> 00:48:59,670
MMM

1308
00:49:00,370 --> 00:49:03,273
-There's no way this is bad.
-It's eel over rice.

1309
00:49:03,340 --> 00:49:04,675
Does it taste like eel?

1310
00:49:04,741 --> 00:49:06,610
Can you taste the eel?

1311
00:49:06,677 --> 00:49:08,245
It's really delicious,

1312
00:49:08,312 --> 00:49:09,513
but it's beef.

1313
00:49:10,547 --> 00:49:12,449
-It doesn't taste like eel, right?
-Right?

1314
00:49:12,516 --> 00:49:14,618
This sweet and salty sauce is so good,

1315
00:49:14,685 --> 00:49:17,154
mixed with egg yolk, onion,

1316
00:49:17,220 --> 00:49:20,057
-and absolutely delicious beef.
-Is that so?

1317
00:49:20,123 --> 00:49:22,292
When you make seasoned eel,
the sauce is very thin,

1318
00:49:22,359 --> 00:49:25,429
and he did just that,
making the sauce rather thin,

1319
00:49:25,495 --> 00:49:27,898
<i>then continuously adding coats</i>
<i>as he grilled it.</i>

1320
00:49:27,965 --> 00:49:29,132
<i>I liked that charred flavor.</i>

1321
00:49:29,199 --> 00:49:32,536
The smokiness fills your mouth
with deliciousness. It was great.

1322
00:49:32,602 --> 00:49:34,638
Next, Chef Sam's dish.

1323
00:49:34,705 --> 00:49:36,873
Stop, You've Won Enough Times.

1324
00:49:37,975 --> 00:49:39,376
MMM

1325
00:49:39,443 --> 00:49:42,980
The chimichurri salad
could make a nice breakfast.

1326
00:49:43,046 --> 00:49:44,848
-It's so tender.
-Yes.

1327
00:49:44,915 --> 00:49:48,618
Although I usually don't enjoy cilantro,

1328
00:49:48,685 --> 00:49:52,522
it tastes refreshing
when I eat it with meat.

1329
00:49:53,190 --> 00:49:54,992
It's like having a salad.

1330
00:49:55,058 --> 00:49:58,662
-It's so tender.
-It looked red, so I thought it was raw.

1331
00:49:58,729 --> 00:50:01,365
But it was tenderly and fully cooked.

1332
00:50:01,431 --> 00:50:03,367
You're such a technician.

1333
00:50:03,433 --> 00:50:05,402
A TECHNICIAN APPROVED BY POONG

1334
00:50:05,602 --> 00:50:08,872
DOWNING THE HOT STONE POT RICE

1335
00:50:08,939 --> 00:50:10,207
I love the balance.

1336
00:50:10,273 --> 00:50:11,274
YUM

1337
00:50:11,341 --> 00:50:12,743
-It's good.
-This sauce is fantastic.

1338
00:50:12,809 --> 00:50:14,511
-It's good.
-The rice is so good.

1339
00:50:14,578 --> 00:50:17,714
It doesn't smell like cilantro,
but mostly like sesame oil,

1340
00:50:17,781 --> 00:50:19,783
-so it reminds me of <i>chamnamul</i>.
-It does.

1341
00:50:19,850 --> 00:50:22,853
-It has that subtle flavor.
-It's similar to <i>chamnamul</i>.

1342
00:50:22,919 --> 00:50:26,890
<i>It's fantastic how you can chew on</i>
<i>some scorched rice with regular rice.</i>

1343
00:50:26,957 --> 00:50:29,926
-I want to try this at home.
-Yes, me too.

1344
00:50:30,794 --> 00:50:32,329
And now, the moment of truth.

1345
00:50:32,396 --> 00:50:34,731
-It's so hard.
-The order you made was

1346
00:50:34,798 --> 00:50:37,634
-A Flashy Dish.
-It must be tough to choose.

1347
00:50:37,701 --> 00:50:39,569
It must've been tough for you too.

1348
00:50:39,636 --> 00:50:40,637
It's so hard.

1349
00:50:40,704 --> 00:50:42,005
<i>Press one for Sam</i>

1350
00:50:42,873 --> 00:50:44,641
<i>and two for Hyun-suk.</i>

1351
00:50:45,308 --> 00:50:47,010
He closes his eyes shut.

1352
00:50:47,077 --> 00:50:48,245
EYES SHUT

1353
00:50:50,313 --> 00:50:51,915
I enjoyed your dish too,

1354
00:50:51,982 --> 00:50:53,050
but I'm so sorry.

1355
00:50:53,116 --> 00:50:55,886
He made his choice.

1356
00:50:55,952 --> 00:50:58,155
Let's find out the result. Show us!

1357
00:50:59,256 --> 00:51:00,991
-A Flashy Dish.
-A Flashy Dish.

1358
00:51:01,058 --> 00:51:02,993
You look so tormented.

1359
00:51:03,060 --> 00:51:06,096
-They were both amazing.
-It tortures you.

1360
00:51:06,163 --> 00:51:08,432
This is their first cook-off this year,

1361
00:51:08,498 --> 00:51:10,467
and they both have two stars.

1362
00:51:10,534 --> 00:51:13,437
Which one of them was the flashier chef?

1363
00:51:13,503 --> 00:51:15,705
Who did Jin-young choose?

1364
00:51:15,772 --> 00:51:16,807
Who is it?

1365
00:51:17,808 --> 00:51:19,843
-Who is it?
-Jin-young's choice!

1366
00:51:19,910 --> 00:51:21,011
Who is it?

1367
00:51:21,211 --> 00:51:23,013
SAM KIM WINS

1368
00:51:23,313 --> 00:51:25,849
CHEF SAM KIM'S
STOP, YOU'VE WON ENOUGH TIMES WINS

1369
00:51:25,916 --> 00:51:27,818
-Sam wins!
-Really?

1370
00:51:27,884 --> 00:51:28,885
Sam Kim!

1371
00:51:28,952 --> 00:51:30,220
SOBS

1372
00:51:30,287 --> 00:51:31,788
Hyun-suk covers his face with his fan.

1373
00:51:31,855 --> 00:51:33,557
THE MASTER HIDES BEHIND HIS FAN

1374
00:51:34,424 --> 00:51:36,326
Sam wins against Hyun-suk

1375
00:51:36,393 --> 00:51:37,461
three rounds in a row,

1376
00:51:37,527 --> 00:51:40,263
-including last year.
-What's going on?

1377
00:51:40,330 --> 00:51:42,466
-It has never happened.
-He keeps his winning streak.

1378
00:51:42,532 --> 00:51:44,601
First, Chef Hyun-suk's dish

1379
00:51:44,668 --> 00:51:47,904
was the most delicious
bowl of rice with toppings

1380
00:51:47,971 --> 00:51:49,639
I have ever had in my life.

1381
00:51:50,440 --> 00:51:51,975
-However…
-However?

1382
00:51:52,042 --> 00:51:53,844
…I had to deduct points

1383
00:51:53,910 --> 00:51:56,680
because it was the kind of flavor
I have had before.

1384
00:51:56,746 --> 00:51:59,216
Chef Sam's dish was something
I have never had before,

1385
00:51:59,282 --> 00:52:03,520
and I didn't know the ingredients I had
could turn into a dish like that.

1386
00:52:03,587 --> 00:52:05,122
Chimichurri did its part.

1387
00:52:05,188 --> 00:52:07,190
-Chimichurri.
-That's true.

1388
00:52:07,257 --> 00:52:11,261
Sam's dish made him go, "This is new.
You can make something like this?"

1389
00:52:11,328 --> 00:52:12,596
Please show us your canine.

1390
00:52:12,929 --> 00:52:14,798
TA-DA

1391
00:52:15,065 --> 00:52:18,235
THE FLASHY CANINE CELEBRATION

1392
00:52:18,301 --> 00:52:20,871
Please put a star on Chef Sam!

1393
00:52:20,937 --> 00:52:24,975
He takes his third star
and ties in first place with Jong-won!

1394
00:52:25,041 --> 00:52:26,409
He's different this year.

1395
00:52:26,476 --> 00:52:29,246
-He's different this year.
-I can't believe this.

1396
00:52:29,312 --> 00:52:32,616
-Thank you.
-No, thank you. It was so delicious.

1397
00:52:32,682 --> 00:52:34,084
The flashy Sam!

1398
00:52:34,151 --> 00:52:36,453
-Your shoes look so cool.
-Congratulations on your third star!

1399
00:52:36,987 --> 00:52:38,889
PREPARING FOR THE COOK-OFF

1400
00:52:40,790 --> 00:52:42,626
I'm so nervous.

1401
00:52:43,293 --> 00:52:44,594
What am I going to do?

1402
00:52:44,661 --> 00:52:46,229
PEAK ANXIETY BEFORE HER FIRST COOK-OFF

1403
00:52:46,296 --> 00:52:49,299
What am I going to do?
I'm more nervous now than on <i>CCW2.</i>

1404
00:52:49,366 --> 00:52:50,767
FLOP

1405
00:52:50,834 --> 00:52:52,169
What do I do?

1406
00:52:52,702 --> 00:52:53,703
WAHHHH

1407
00:52:53,770 --> 00:52:55,438
-It's all right.
-You know that feeling?

1408
00:52:55,505 --> 00:52:56,840
-A racing heart.
-Yeah, I do.

1409
00:52:56,907 --> 00:52:59,409
-It's four times as nerve-racking as <i>CCW</i>.
-You can do it.

1410
00:52:59,476 --> 00:53:01,645
-Don't get hurt.
-Okay.

1411
00:53:01,711 --> 00:53:03,680
Let's do our best.

1412
00:53:04,948 --> 00:53:08,985
<i>Let us begin the second round</i>
<i>with ingredients from Jin-young's fridge.</i>

1413
00:53:09,052 --> 00:53:11,621
Here to gnaw away at Poong with a rawr,

1414
00:53:11,688 --> 00:53:14,224
Little Tiger, Kim Si-hyeon

1415
00:53:14,291 --> 00:53:17,360
versus Kim Poong,
who's here to make her bawl,

1416
00:53:17,427 --> 00:53:20,864
also known as the Old Beastly Dude.

1417
00:53:20,931 --> 00:53:22,632
TIGER VERSUS BEAST

1418
00:53:22,699 --> 00:53:24,134
He reminds me of a nutria.

1419
00:53:24,467 --> 00:53:27,537
THE BEASTLY NUTRIA BULLIES LITTLE TIGER

1420
00:53:28,138 --> 00:53:29,539
How scary.

1421
00:53:29,606 --> 00:53:33,143
Today is finally the day
when a new chef from <i>CCW</i>

1422
00:53:33,210 --> 00:53:36,613
stands here up against Kim Poong,
the Cook of the Darkness.

1423
00:53:36,680 --> 00:53:38,381
-You also grew up with the show.
-I have.

1424
00:53:38,448 --> 00:53:40,684
You probably never imagined

1425
00:53:40,750 --> 00:53:44,888
-you'd be standing here to cook.
-It's so weird that my name is up there.

1426
00:53:44,955 --> 00:53:47,023
-Don't you feel proud?
-Yes, it's so cool!

1427
00:53:47,090 --> 00:53:48,191
HOW CUTE

1428
00:53:48,258 --> 00:53:49,859
Your mom is going to be thrilled.

1429
00:53:49,926 --> 00:53:53,029
Many people said this
after watching <i>Culinary Class Wars 2.</i>

1430
00:53:53,096 --> 00:53:54,965
"You may win, or you may be eliminated,

1431
00:53:55,031 --> 00:53:57,467
but all roads will lead to Kim Poong."

1432
00:53:57,534 --> 00:54:00,503
-That's right.
-He's our gatekeeper.

1433
00:54:00,570 --> 00:54:04,074
Poong, I'm sure
you also feel different about this round.

1434
00:54:04,140 --> 00:54:05,909
First of all, I won't go easy on her.

1435
00:54:05,976 --> 00:54:07,377
-I knew it.
-First time? Whatever.

1436
00:54:07,444 --> 00:54:11,214
-Handle her for us.
-Little Tiger, I'm going to take you…

1437
00:54:11,281 --> 00:54:12,415
Okay?

1438
00:54:12,482 --> 00:54:14,584
…and make you shudder in fear!

1439
00:54:14,985 --> 00:54:16,686
WATCHING SOMETHING UNSIGHTLY IN PERSON

1440
00:54:16,753 --> 00:54:18,021
How scary.

1441
00:54:18,655 --> 00:54:21,925
The young guns probably can connect.
Why don't you encourage her?

1442
00:54:21,992 --> 00:54:25,161
Even one-star Michelin chefs come here
and cook with trembling hands.

1443
00:54:25,228 --> 00:54:27,931
-Yes, of course.
-Is he talking about me?

1444
00:54:27,998 --> 00:54:30,133
I hope you make a wonderful dish.

1445
00:54:30,200 --> 00:54:32,002
Do you have anything to say, Sung-jun?

1446
00:54:32,068 --> 00:54:35,505
I'm the rational type,
so let me give her practical tips.

1447
00:54:35,572 --> 00:54:37,674
If he tries your food
after trying Poong's food,

1448
00:54:37,741 --> 00:54:39,309
it may not taste like anything.

1449
00:54:39,376 --> 00:54:41,945
It's important that you finish first.

1450
00:54:42,012 --> 00:54:44,180
-Okay.
-That's a great tip.

1451
00:54:44,247 --> 00:54:46,283
-Chef Eun-yeong, a word, please.
-He's so rational.

1452
00:54:46,349 --> 00:54:50,120
The chefs here will
continue to talk and try to disturb you.

1453
00:54:50,186 --> 00:54:51,821
I'll use my shotgun when they do.

1454
00:54:53,390 --> 00:54:54,491
You don't shoot shotguns like this.

1455
00:54:54,791 --> 00:54:56,092
I DO

1456
00:54:56,159 --> 00:54:58,228
It was a shotgun? Not a blowgun?

1457
00:54:58,528 --> 00:55:00,930
EMBARRASSED

1458
00:55:00,997 --> 00:55:02,766
She does it like this,

1459
00:55:02,832 --> 00:55:04,534
but she said it's a shotgun.

1460
00:55:04,601 --> 00:55:06,703
I'll shoot them with whatever I can.

1461
00:55:06,770 --> 00:55:08,438
You seem rather nervous,

1462
00:55:08,505 --> 00:55:11,241
but you also said you felt confident
about this particular order.

1463
00:55:11,308 --> 00:55:13,476
Yes, it's titled Carrot Heaven,

1464
00:55:13,543 --> 00:55:17,113
and I'm quite confident
when it comes to vegetables.

1465
00:55:17,180 --> 00:55:18,982
-She loves <i>namul</i>.
-I know its characteristics.

1466
00:55:19,049 --> 00:55:22,585
I love seeing
this kind of confidence. Yes.

1467
00:55:22,652 --> 00:55:25,422
-You're good today. You're funny.
-I want to fight someone confident,

1468
00:55:25,488 --> 00:55:28,258
-not someone who feels timid.
-Of course not.

1469
00:55:28,325 --> 00:55:29,959
-I love it.
-I see.

1470
00:55:30,026 --> 00:55:32,696
For the first-timers
of the 15-minute cook-off,

1471
00:55:32,762 --> 00:55:36,166
-we offer a perk you can use.
-Yes, that's right.

1472
00:55:36,232 --> 00:55:38,134
-Gosh, I'm so glad.
-There are three kinds.

1473
00:55:38,201 --> 00:55:39,936
You can either start a minute first,

1474
00:55:40,003 --> 00:55:42,072
stop your opponent for a minute,

1475
00:55:42,138 --> 00:55:44,240
or initiate UNICHEF for a minute.

1476
00:55:44,307 --> 00:55:47,010
You can choose one of the three.

1477
00:55:47,577 --> 00:55:49,913
I'll go with UNICHEF.

1478
00:55:49,979 --> 00:55:52,015
-UNICHEF.
-What a relief.

1479
00:55:52,082 --> 00:55:54,551
-That's the best for me.
-Your role model is here.

1480
00:55:54,617 --> 00:55:57,220
-Your role model.
-You can pick out just one chef.

1481
00:55:57,754 --> 00:55:59,189
LOOKING AROUND

1482
00:55:59,255 --> 00:56:01,758
The one who took some time off,
Chef Nam-no.

1483
00:56:01,825 --> 00:56:03,893
-It's Chef Nam-no.
-Don't blame me for anything.

1484
00:56:03,960 --> 00:56:06,029
You'd better not blame me!

1485
00:56:06,096 --> 00:56:08,631
You'll have to come with me
for the five-minute check too.

1486
00:56:09,432 --> 00:56:11,468
-You'll be busy.
-I'm even busier than usual.

1487
00:56:11,534 --> 00:56:12,669
You'll be busy.

1488
00:56:13,603 --> 00:56:17,774
CHEF SI-HYEON'S INGREDIENTS:
CARROT, CILANTRO, HONEY, RICE

1489
00:56:17,841 --> 00:56:20,610
Chef Si-hyeon, what are you making?

1490
00:56:21,511 --> 00:56:22,512
GLANCING

1491
00:56:22,579 --> 00:56:26,316
-Came to Carrot Poong.
-That was so cute.

1492
00:56:26,583 --> 00:56:27,984
YOU'RE DOING GREAT

1493
00:56:28,051 --> 00:56:30,220
-All right!
-Carrot!

1494
00:56:31,388 --> 00:56:33,356
-Came to Carrot Poong.
-I'm so angry.

1495
00:56:33,423 --> 00:56:34,491
HEHE

1496
00:56:34,557 --> 00:56:36,059
Doing that is harder than cooking.

1497
00:56:36,126 --> 00:56:38,094
How do you plan to make this?

1498
00:56:38,161 --> 00:56:42,365
Carrots have a nice, sweet flavor
once they're steamed,

1499
00:56:42,432 --> 00:56:45,335
-so I'll make <i>tteok</i>, rice cake, with it.
-Carrot <i>tteok</i>?

1500
00:56:45,402 --> 00:56:48,071
I'm going to make dried carrot shavings.

1501
00:56:48,138 --> 00:56:50,473
-Dried shavings?
-Like dried pumpkin shavings,

1502
00:56:50,540 --> 00:56:51,541
but with carrots.

1503
00:56:51,608 --> 00:56:55,578
I'll use raw carrots to create the texture
of dried carrots for the dish.

1504
00:56:55,645 --> 00:56:56,646
It sounds hard.

1505
00:56:56,713 --> 00:56:58,615
Also, since he likes cilantro,

1506
00:56:58,681 --> 00:57:01,084
I'll pickle some carrots with them.

1507
00:57:01,151 --> 00:57:05,121
I want him to enjoy
the fragrance of raw carrots,

1508
00:57:05,188 --> 00:57:06,656
so I'll also make carrot honey.

1509
00:57:06,723 --> 00:57:09,559
-Carrot honey.
-Will she mix carrot juice with honey?

1510
00:57:09,626 --> 00:57:10,727
Three dishes?

1511
00:57:10,794 --> 00:57:11,961
She should do that.

1512
00:57:12,028 --> 00:57:13,129
I'll do my best.

1513
00:57:13,196 --> 00:57:15,198
-I hope it goes well.
-She's a tiger.

1514
00:57:16,132 --> 00:57:17,934
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S INGREDIENTS:

1515
00:57:18,001 --> 00:57:20,203
CARROT, CILANTRO,
GLUTINOUS RICE POWDER, CREAM CHEESE

1516
00:57:20,270 --> 00:57:22,405
The name of my dish is as follows.

1517
00:57:23,039 --> 00:57:26,009
I'll Make Carrot With Carrot.

1518
00:57:27,110 --> 00:57:29,379
-You're good.
-You're good at that.

1519
00:57:29,646 --> 00:57:31,080
COPIED MASTER HU DEOK-JUK PERFECTLY

1520
00:57:31,147 --> 00:57:32,816
"That carrot must be delicious."

1521
00:57:32,882 --> 00:57:37,153
I'll mix carrots
with glutinous rice powder

1522
00:57:37,220 --> 00:57:40,523
and make a sweet carrot donut.

1523
00:57:40,590 --> 00:57:42,091
"It sounds delicious."

1524
00:57:42,158 --> 00:57:43,460
I think he'll do something big.

1525
00:57:43,526 --> 00:57:46,463
-Also, carrot cream.
-Carrot cream.

1526
00:57:46,529 --> 00:57:47,931
I'll make smooth carrot cream

1527
00:57:47,997 --> 00:57:51,034
and let him enjoy the donut
with the cream.

1528
00:57:51,100 --> 00:57:52,969
And it'll also look like a carrot.

1529
00:57:53,770 --> 00:57:56,606
-A carrot-shaped donut.
-He'll shape it.

1530
00:57:56,673 --> 00:57:58,508
You won't deep-fry it whole, right?

1531
00:57:58,575 --> 00:58:00,510
-No way.
-Not the whole carrot.

1532
00:58:00,577 --> 00:58:02,178
That's not a donut! That's a carrot!

1533
00:58:02,245 --> 00:58:04,914
You might coat a carrot with batter.

1534
00:58:04,981 --> 00:58:06,950
That's not a bad idea.

1535
00:58:07,016 --> 00:58:08,518
-So no? Okay.
-No.

1536
00:58:08,585 --> 00:58:09,786
I'll look forward to it.

1537
00:58:09,853 --> 00:58:10,854
My gosh.

1538
00:58:10,920 --> 00:58:14,390
Let us begin this round, Carrot Heaven.

1539
00:58:14,457 --> 00:58:17,227
-You got this!
-She must be so nervous.

1540
00:58:17,293 --> 00:58:19,829
Welcome, it's your first time
fighting against Kim Poong.

1541
00:58:19,896 --> 00:58:22,565
The Old Beastly Dude

1542
00:58:22,632 --> 00:58:25,502
who'll make Little Tiger wail,
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.

1543
00:58:25,568 --> 00:58:29,873
But she'll turn the Old Beastly Dude
into the Old Silly Dude,

1544
00:58:29,939 --> 00:58:33,343
Little Tiger, Kim Si-hyeon.

1545
00:58:33,409 --> 00:58:36,379
The road to Kim Poong!
Who'll rise as the winner?

1546
00:58:36,446 --> 00:58:39,148
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1547
00:58:39,215 --> 00:58:40,216
Hurry up.

1548
00:58:41,184 --> 00:58:42,252
LET'S GO!

1549
00:58:42,318 --> 00:58:44,487
-Please come.
-Already?

1550
00:58:45,288 --> 00:58:47,023
-Hurry.
-The minute begins.

1551
00:58:47,090 --> 00:58:48,091
Watch your hand.

1552
00:58:48,157 --> 00:58:50,260
She uses UNICHEF right away.

1553
00:58:50,326 --> 00:58:51,961
-Should I make rice powder?
-That's right.

1554
00:58:52,028 --> 00:58:54,731
Chef Si-hyeon uses UNICHEF right away.

1555
00:58:54,797 --> 00:58:56,432
So he's grinding soaked rice?

1556
00:58:56,499 --> 00:58:57,767
Watch your hand.

1557
00:58:57,834 --> 00:59:01,471
She's going to make steamed rice cake
with those carrots.

1558
00:59:01,538 --> 00:59:03,106
-Don't you need water?
-Just like that?

1559
00:59:03,172 --> 00:59:05,241
-It's been soaked.
-It's already been soaked.

1560
00:59:05,308 --> 00:59:08,711
-She asked him to grind something.
-Rice powder.

1561
00:59:09,846 --> 00:59:11,848
-Should I sift it?
-Yes, please do.

1562
00:59:11,915 --> 00:59:14,150
-Like this?
-That's correct.

1563
00:59:14,217 --> 00:59:17,253
You have 20 more seconds of UNICHEF.

1564
00:59:17,320 --> 00:59:19,222
Carrot rice cake? I can't imagine it.

1565
00:59:19,622 --> 00:59:21,324
CHOP!

1566
00:59:21,391 --> 00:59:23,192
That's some great chopping.

1567
00:59:23,526 --> 00:59:24,561
LOVES IT

1568
00:59:24,627 --> 00:59:27,964
-It's not even at all.
-"Chop!"

1569
00:59:28,031 --> 00:59:30,433
-He'll grind it anyway.
-Yes, he'll grind it.

1570
00:59:30,500 --> 00:59:32,569
Don't you need water?

1571
00:59:32,635 --> 00:59:34,737
-Can you grind it?
-He grinds a carrot.

1572
00:59:34,804 --> 00:59:36,039
It works so well.

1573
00:59:36,105 --> 00:59:37,507
It worked well.

1574
00:59:37,574 --> 00:59:41,244
-Poong just ground a carrot.
-What will he do with it?

1575
00:59:41,311 --> 00:59:44,981
Now, she said
she'd make dried carrot slices.

1576
00:59:45,048 --> 00:59:46,115
COOKING OIL

1577
00:59:46,349 --> 00:59:48,017
LOTS OF OIL!

1578
00:59:48,084 --> 00:59:49,852
Two. One.

1579
00:59:49,919 --> 00:59:51,254
He made rice powder.

1580
00:59:51,321 --> 00:59:52,555
-Here.
-All right.

1581
00:59:52,622 --> 00:59:53,756
-UNICHEF ends.
-Thank you!

1582
00:59:53,823 --> 00:59:56,259
-I'm fine.
-It's been a minute. Come back, Nam-no.

1583
00:59:56,326 --> 00:59:58,328
She just sliced the carrots.

1584
00:59:58,394 --> 01:00:02,065
-What's she doing?
-Will she reduce it down?

1585
01:00:02,131 --> 01:00:03,132
-She's putting it in oil.
-Is she deep-frying those?

1586
01:00:03,199 --> 01:00:04,500
-Yes, it's oil.
-As if she's deep-frying.

1587
01:00:04,567 --> 01:00:06,636
She's doing it over low heat.

1588
01:00:07,036 --> 01:00:09,372
NEXT, CHECK OUT HER CHOPPING SKILLS

1589
01:00:09,572 --> 01:00:11,040
IMMACULATE RHYTHM!

1590
01:00:11,341 --> 01:00:12,875
She's a lefty.

1591
01:00:12,942 --> 01:00:14,310
-Huh?
-She is.

1592
01:00:14,377 --> 01:00:15,378
Just like you.

1593
01:00:15,445 --> 01:00:16,646
I'm a lefty too.

1594
01:00:16,713 --> 01:00:18,147
She is? I'm also a lefty.

1595
01:00:18,214 --> 01:00:19,949
-Poong is a lefty too.
-Everyone is.

1596
01:00:20,016 --> 01:00:21,551
-Poong's a lefty too.
-He is?

1597
01:00:21,618 --> 01:00:23,686
It's a cook-off between lefties.

1598
01:00:26,422 --> 01:00:27,423
UNEXPECTED COMMENTARY!

1599
01:00:27,490 --> 01:00:28,825
Is it any different?

1600
01:00:28,891 --> 01:00:31,828
-Does he just throw everything out there?
-Yes.

1601
01:00:31,894 --> 01:00:33,630
I just throw it out there.

1602
01:00:33,696 --> 01:00:36,165
-Singer Lee Juck must be happy.
-Sure.

1603
01:00:36,232 --> 01:00:38,935
-Lee Juck must be very happy.
-Sure.

1604
01:00:39,002 --> 01:00:40,637
SLICED AND COVERED WITH PLASTIC

1605
01:00:40,703 --> 01:00:42,805
Hurry up.

1606
01:00:42,872 --> 01:00:44,641
He popped it into the microwave.

1607
01:00:45,074 --> 01:00:46,643
THE CARROT HE GROUND EARLIER!

1608
01:00:46,709 --> 01:00:49,479
-It looks like salmon roe.
-Yes, the color.

1609
01:00:49,545 --> 01:00:52,615
3. COOK GROUND CARROT, SALT, SUGAR,
AND BUTTER IN THE MICROWAVE

1610
01:00:53,516 --> 01:00:54,784
Time flies like crazy.

1611
01:00:54,851 --> 01:00:56,819
Are you using the microwave?

1612
01:00:56,886 --> 01:00:58,721
-Microphone what?
-The microwave.

1613
01:00:58,788 --> 01:01:00,056
-I'm not.
-Good.

1614
01:01:00,123 --> 01:01:02,025
"Microphone what?"

1615
01:01:02,091 --> 01:01:03,826
-May I use it?
-Stop bothering her.

1616
01:01:03,893 --> 01:01:05,428
Why won't you use it?

1617
01:01:05,495 --> 01:01:07,063
Are you using her microwave too?

1618
01:01:07,130 --> 01:01:08,431
CARROTS IN BOTH MICROWAVES!

1619
01:01:09,766 --> 01:01:11,868
Webtoon Artist Poong uses both microwaves.

1620
01:01:11,934 --> 01:01:14,904
Or maybe his is empty,
and he's using hers just to shake her up.

1621
01:01:14,971 --> 01:01:16,372
HEHEHE

1622
01:01:16,939 --> 01:01:19,776
What's she going to do
after deep-frying the carrot slices?

1623
01:01:19,842 --> 01:01:21,110
-I wonder.
-Are those toppings?

1624
01:01:21,177 --> 01:01:23,079
Will you add those between the <i>tteok?</i>

1625
01:01:23,146 --> 01:01:25,148
-You're right.
-I see.

1626
01:01:25,214 --> 01:01:26,282
Three minutes have passed.

1627
01:01:26,349 --> 01:01:30,086
Carrot cake is the only thing I've had
that uses carrots as its main ingredient.

1628
01:01:30,753 --> 01:01:32,722
-Are those dried carrot slices?
-Hurry.

1629
01:01:32,789 --> 01:01:35,391
I need to hurry.
There's not enough time. First, sugar.

1630
01:01:35,458 --> 01:01:37,827
He's adding sugar and salt
into glutinous rice powder.

1631
01:01:37,894 --> 01:01:39,929
I see. He's using glutinous rice powder.

1632
01:01:39,996 --> 01:01:41,364
He's making an old-fashioned donut.

1633
01:01:41,431 --> 01:01:44,734
It looks like Chef Si-hyeon
is ready to make <i>tteok</i>, rice cake.

1634
01:01:44,801 --> 01:01:47,170
-She mixed salt, rice powder, and carrot.
-I see.

1635
01:01:47,236 --> 01:01:48,871
She seasons it a little.

1636
01:01:49,739 --> 01:01:52,108
Poong needs to make donuts.

1637
01:01:52,775 --> 01:01:53,776
TOO HOT

1638
01:01:54,744 --> 01:01:57,280
-It's not cooked.
-What now?

1639
01:01:57,346 --> 01:01:59,415
When carrots are undercooked,

1640
01:01:59,482 --> 01:02:02,819
they'll still feel crunchy
even after they're finely ground.

1641
01:02:02,885 --> 01:02:05,021
So it must be cooked thoroughly
to make cream.

1642
01:02:05,088 --> 01:02:07,757
-He's still not using any water.
-Is he grinding that again?

1643
01:02:07,824 --> 01:02:08,825
Will it work?

1644
01:02:08,891 --> 01:02:11,461
-Wait…
-Can't you add some water?

1645
01:02:12,328 --> 01:02:14,931
-Are you sure everything is planned?
-Planned?

1646
01:02:14,997 --> 01:02:16,733
-What plan?
-You have 11 minutes left.

1647
01:02:17,300 --> 01:02:18,868
It's been four minutes.

1648
01:02:18,935 --> 01:02:21,337
He's making donuts.
It's <i>tteok</i> versus donuts.

1649
01:02:21,404 --> 01:02:23,106
-You have no time.
-You have ten minutes.

1650
01:02:23,172 --> 01:02:24,741
-Okay.
-Wow.

1651
01:02:24,807 --> 01:02:28,044
-They're both making dough.
-The methods seem similar.

1652
01:02:28,111 --> 01:02:31,948
She ground everything finely,
so the color turned orange.

1653
01:02:32,014 --> 01:02:36,219
But his carrots weren't cooked
or finely ground, so they're in chunks.

1654
01:02:36,285 --> 01:02:37,286
YOU'RE RIGHT

1655
01:02:37,353 --> 01:02:40,089
So it won't turn out reddish,
but will contain chunks of carrot.

1656
01:02:40,156 --> 01:02:41,958
You're right.

1657
01:02:42,024 --> 01:02:44,627
Shouldn't you have cooked it longer?
Is that okay, Poong?

1658
01:02:44,694 --> 01:02:47,263
It's okay. I can mash it as I knead.

1659
01:02:47,330 --> 01:02:50,066
-He's mashing it.
-He's strong.

1660
01:02:52,101 --> 01:02:53,269
She's staying calm.

1661
01:02:53,336 --> 01:02:54,337
Good job.

1662
01:02:54,403 --> 01:02:55,404
STRAINING OIL

1663
01:02:55,638 --> 01:02:56,939
NEXT, JUST THE CARROT SLICES!

1664
01:02:57,540 --> 01:02:59,742
-Soy sauce? Just a little?
-Soy sauce.

1665
01:02:59,809 --> 01:03:01,177
Where's the honey?

1666
01:03:01,410 --> 01:03:03,012
RIGHT BEFORE HER EYES!

1667
01:03:03,079 --> 01:03:05,148
Honey. That's what you're doing.

1668
01:03:05,214 --> 01:03:08,484
-Like <i>jeonggwa</i>, candied fruit.
-Like <i>jeonggwa</i>.

1669
01:03:08,551 --> 01:03:10,019
-Candied carrot.
-Must be good.

1670
01:03:10,086 --> 01:03:11,387
Is she making it sweet?

1671
01:03:11,454 --> 01:03:12,855
"It must be delicious."

1672
01:03:12,922 --> 01:03:14,657
"It must be delicious."

1673
01:03:14,724 --> 01:03:16,826
She's making the carrot slices sweet
like <i>jeonggwa</i>.

1674
01:03:17,994 --> 01:03:20,863
She's like a tiger when she cooks.

1675
01:03:20,930 --> 01:03:22,498
-She's a tiger.
-A tiger.

1676
01:03:22,565 --> 01:03:24,167
Chef Si-hyeon's eyes have gone crazy.

1677
01:03:24,567 --> 01:03:26,269
RAWR!

1678
01:03:26,335 --> 01:03:27,503
Her eyes look crazy.

1679
01:03:27,570 --> 01:03:30,139
It looks like the dough
isn't working out for Poong.

1680
01:03:30,807 --> 01:03:32,208
He adds water.

1681
01:03:32,275 --> 01:03:35,745
He's working on the dough,
but it's not going smoothly.

1682
01:03:35,812 --> 01:03:37,213
Poong, you have ten minutes.

1683
01:03:37,280 --> 01:03:39,182
Ten minutes? Okay.

1684
01:03:39,248 --> 01:03:40,249
HUFFING AND PUFFING

1685
01:03:40,650 --> 01:03:41,751
10 MINUTES?

1686
01:03:42,318 --> 01:03:44,153
SI-HYEON IS READY TO STEAM THE TTEOK!

1687
01:03:44,520 --> 01:03:45,688
THROWS IN SQUARE MOLDS

1688
01:03:46,088 --> 01:03:48,191
FILLS WITH RICE POWDER DOUGH

1689
01:03:48,257 --> 01:03:50,393
Chef Si-hyeon is making them
similar to <i>siru-tteok</i>.

1690
01:03:50,459 --> 01:03:52,061
She's making steamed <i>tteok</i> called <i>seolgi</i>.

1691
01:03:52,128 --> 01:03:54,597
-<i>Seolgi</i>.
-Carrot <i>seolgi</i>.

1692
01:03:54,664 --> 01:03:56,232
Like white rice <i>seolgi</i>, right?

1693
01:03:56,799 --> 01:03:59,535
It doesn't seem like
her <i>tteok</i> will be too big.

1694
01:03:59,602 --> 01:04:02,605
-It's as small as a one-serving <i>tteok</i>.
-Right?

1695
01:04:02,672 --> 01:04:05,107
The ones that are individually wrapped.

1696
01:04:05,174 --> 01:04:06,475
SHE BEGINS TO STEAM THEM!

1697
01:04:07,510 --> 01:04:10,046
-She cleans up as she cooks.
-Yes.

1698
01:04:10,613 --> 01:04:12,181
PHEW
SHE GOT THROUGH THE FIRST OBSTACLE!

1699
01:04:12,248 --> 01:04:13,816
I hope they get steamed nicely.

1700
01:04:14,617 --> 01:04:15,718
POONG IS STILL KNEADING

1701
01:04:15,785 --> 01:04:18,788
Can Poong successfully serve the donut?

1702
01:04:18,855 --> 01:04:20,823
He said he'd make it look like a carrot.

1703
01:04:20,890 --> 01:04:23,226
-Look at Chef Si-hyeon.
-Is she done?

1704
01:04:23,292 --> 01:04:25,595
-Lower the heat.
-There's too much water.

1705
01:04:25,661 --> 01:04:28,030
-There's too much water.
-No! It's wet!

1706
01:04:28,097 --> 01:04:29,365
The water! What will you do?

1707
01:04:29,432 --> 01:04:31,868
-It'll make the <i>tteok</i> mushy.
-Oh, no. It got mushy.

1708
01:04:31,934 --> 01:04:34,704
-It'll make it mushy.
-She should drain some water.

1709
01:04:34,770 --> 01:04:36,772
Either remove some water
or lower the heat!

1710
01:04:36,839 --> 01:04:38,507
Goodness, Chef Si-hyeon!

1711
01:04:38,574 --> 01:04:40,209
-She got it.
-It's all right.

1712
01:04:40,276 --> 01:04:42,745
-She's fine.
-She learned that from Sung-jun.

1713
01:04:43,012 --> 01:04:44,013
LIKE A SENIOR CHEF

1714
01:04:44,380 --> 01:04:45,748
CALM TIGER

1715
01:04:45,815 --> 01:04:46,816
CALMLY SCOOPS WATER OUT

1716
01:04:46,883 --> 01:04:47,884
CHECKS THE TIME

1717
01:04:48,284 --> 01:04:49,452
What is it?

1718
01:04:49,518 --> 01:04:52,221
-It got mushy, so I need to remake it.
-One more? Okay.

1719
01:04:52,288 --> 01:04:53,956
Did one get ruined?

1720
01:04:54,023 --> 01:04:58,027
-It touched the water when it shouldn't.
-I see. It touched the water.

1721
01:04:58,094 --> 01:04:59,095
I see.

1722
01:04:59,161 --> 01:05:00,863
-She's remaking them.
-She has enough time.

1723
01:05:00,930 --> 01:05:02,899
-The water.
-You can do it! You can do it, Si-hyeon!

1724
01:05:02,965 --> 01:05:05,301
-You got this! You can!
-Like that?

1725
01:05:05,368 --> 01:05:07,603
You can do this. And I can do it too.

1726
01:05:08,170 --> 01:05:09,639
Can you put him to sleep?

1727
01:05:10,473 --> 01:05:11,474
I can do it too! I can--

1728
01:05:11,741 --> 01:05:13,309
PERFECT TEAMWORK

1729
01:05:15,378 --> 01:05:17,580
RESURRECTED LIKE A BEAST!

1730
01:05:17,647 --> 01:05:20,583
I can do this! I'll win!

1731
01:05:20,650 --> 01:05:22,184
THE DOUGH DEVIL RUNS AMOK

1732
01:05:22,251 --> 01:05:23,653
-Are you okay?
-I can win!

1733
01:05:24,320 --> 01:05:26,355
Gosh. Hey, stop it.

1734
01:05:26,422 --> 01:05:29,058
-You're embarrassing us.
-He says he's embarrassing us.

1735
01:05:29,125 --> 01:05:30,593
You're embarrassing us.

1736
01:05:30,660 --> 01:05:32,395
VIEWERS,
WE APOLOGIZE ON HIS BEHALF

1737
01:05:32,461 --> 01:05:33,729
LOL

1738
01:05:34,664 --> 01:05:36,032
-He's embarrassed.
-He's embarrassing us.

1739
01:05:36,098 --> 01:05:37,400
Why is he doing this?

1740
01:05:37,466 --> 01:05:39,101
He's so embarrassing.

1741
01:05:39,969 --> 01:05:42,238
TAKES OUT COOKED CARROTS
FROM THE MICROWAVE

1742
01:05:43,372 --> 01:05:44,573
IT'LL TURN INTO CARROT CREAM

1743
01:05:44,774 --> 01:05:47,243
GROUND CARROT, SUGAR, SALT, BUTTER

1744
01:05:47,310 --> 01:05:48,411
Let's blend it.

1745
01:05:48,477 --> 01:05:49,679
It's hot.

1746
01:05:49,745 --> 01:05:51,580
Is that flying fish roe?

1747
01:05:51,647 --> 01:05:53,182
Flying fish roe?

1748
01:05:53,549 --> 01:05:54,550
6. BLEND IT FINELY

1749
01:05:54,617 --> 01:05:55,818
What are you up to, Poong?

1750
01:05:55,885 --> 01:05:58,988
I'm making this into carrot cream.

1751
01:05:59,055 --> 01:06:00,756
You're making carrot cream?

1752
01:06:00,823 --> 01:06:04,293
He's making sauce for the donut.

1753
01:06:04,360 --> 01:06:05,695
Yes, carrot cream.

1754
01:06:05,761 --> 01:06:07,730
No matter how finely the carrot is ground,

1755
01:06:07,797 --> 01:06:10,800
-it'll remain crisp if it isn't cooked.
-That's true.

1756
01:06:11,033 --> 01:06:12,268
THEN I'LL HAVE IT COOKED!

1757
01:06:12,335 --> 01:06:14,036
It's important to cook them thoroughly.

1758
01:06:14,103 --> 01:06:16,038
Now he's boiling it in a pan.

1759
01:06:16,105 --> 01:06:18,541
Can you see the carrot lumps?

1760
01:06:18,607 --> 01:06:21,010
It has to be smoother,
but it's not cooked thoroughly.

1761
01:06:21,644 --> 01:06:23,746
-What's that?
-Cream cheese.

1762
01:06:23,813 --> 01:06:26,248
-He's adding cream cheese?
-He's cooking it now.

1763
01:06:26,315 --> 01:06:27,883
Vinegar and salt…

1764
01:06:27,950 --> 01:06:29,318
Pickling juice?

1765
01:06:29,618 --> 01:06:32,288
SI-HYEON STARTS MAKING CARROT PICKLES

1766
01:06:32,855 --> 01:06:34,023
Pickles, okay.

1767
01:06:34,090 --> 01:06:35,191
CILANTRO STEM

1768
01:06:35,691 --> 01:06:39,395
8. POUR VINEGAR, SALT, SUGAR, CILANTRO MIX
OVER JULIENNED CARROT

1769
01:06:39,462 --> 01:06:41,197
What else are you doing again?

1770
01:06:41,263 --> 01:06:42,832
-Carrot honey.
-Carrot honey?

1771
01:06:42,898 --> 01:06:45,935
-But these are already sweet, so…
-Just a bit?

1772
01:06:46,802 --> 01:06:49,005
Too much honey
will bring out more moisture.

1773
01:06:49,071 --> 01:06:50,906
She can even explain her dish to us.

1774
01:06:50,973 --> 01:06:52,241
-She's relaxed.
-She is.

1775
01:06:52,308 --> 01:06:53,776
-She's calmer than us.
-Yes.

1776
01:06:53,843 --> 01:06:55,144
-What's going on?
-I wonder.

1777
01:06:55,211 --> 01:06:57,780
They both seem relaxed.
Is the <i>tteok</i> ready?

1778
01:06:57,847 --> 01:06:58,848
Hey, the rice cake.

1779
01:06:58,914 --> 01:07:00,383
I don't think it's ready yet.

1780
01:07:01,250 --> 01:07:02,485
You got this!

1781
01:07:02,551 --> 01:07:05,888
-You got this!
-You got this! Don't get flustered.

1782
01:07:05,955 --> 01:07:07,056
Otherwise, it's all over.

1783
01:07:07,123 --> 01:07:09,959
-I'm not flustered. I'm not.
-You can do this.

1784
01:07:10,026 --> 01:07:12,261
-Why won't the dough work?
-You're the one who's flustered.

1785
01:07:12,328 --> 01:07:14,096
Dang it, dough! Why won't you work?

1786
01:07:14,163 --> 01:07:15,798
Can he turn that into donuts?

1787
01:07:15,865 --> 01:07:18,000
It turned orange, at least.

1788
01:07:18,067 --> 01:07:20,069
If I don't knead it well, it'll pop.

1789
01:07:20,136 --> 01:07:21,337
-That's true.
-Yes.

1790
01:07:21,404 --> 01:07:23,839
-Donuts are all about the dough.
-Yes.

1791
01:07:23,906 --> 01:07:25,875
And you said you'd shape it like a carrot.

1792
01:07:25,941 --> 01:07:28,377
There are five minutes left.
Please report from the kitchen.

1793
01:07:28,844 --> 01:07:31,080
REPORTED BY JUNG-HWAN AND NAM-NO

1794
01:07:31,147 --> 01:07:32,848
Let me give this dough a go.

1795
01:07:32,915 --> 01:07:36,452
-He'll have to deep-fry that.
-Can she win her first star?

1796
01:07:36,519 --> 01:07:38,721
-Is that carrot honey <i>tteok</i>… No.
-Carrot honey.

1797
01:07:38,788 --> 01:07:39,789
Carrot honey.

1798
01:07:39,855 --> 01:07:42,024
I've never seen carrot honey before.

1799
01:07:42,091 --> 01:07:44,460
Let's go, carrot.

1800
01:07:45,194 --> 01:07:47,063
It doesn't look like a carrot.

1801
01:07:47,129 --> 01:07:49,331
-That's a carrot?
-That's a carrot?

1802
01:07:49,398 --> 01:07:51,167
AN AWFULLY FAMILIAR SHAPE

1803
01:07:51,233 --> 01:07:52,802
-Gosh.
-You said it'd look like a carrot.

1804
01:07:52,868 --> 01:07:55,171
-We'll have to wait until it's done.
-Okay.

1805
01:07:55,237 --> 01:07:56,605
He claims that it's a carrot.

1806
01:07:56,672 --> 01:07:58,941
-May I try this?
-That one. The cream.

1807
01:07:59,008 --> 01:08:03,145
-This cream, the donut sauce.
-Look at that shape.

1808
01:08:03,212 --> 01:08:04,980
Carrot cream.

1809
01:08:05,047 --> 01:08:08,317
-Let us try the carrot cream.
-Nam-no tries the carrot cream.

1810
01:08:08,384 --> 01:08:11,487
-Carrot cream.
-Can he take Little Tiger down?

1811
01:08:12,688 --> 01:08:15,157
-Can he take Little Tiger down?
-Can he?

1812
01:08:15,224 --> 01:08:18,127
We're seeing the second
Poongphobia patient in the making.

1813
01:08:18,727 --> 01:08:20,196
AHHHH!

1814
01:08:20,262 --> 01:08:21,797
…in the making.

1815
01:08:21,864 --> 01:08:23,499
ROAR!

1816
01:08:23,566 --> 01:08:24,834
THE BEAST IS HERE!

1817
01:08:24,900 --> 01:08:26,735
It must taste quite nice.

1818
01:08:26,802 --> 01:08:28,137
ARRRGH!

1819
01:08:28,204 --> 01:08:29,872
ARR!

1820
01:08:29,939 --> 01:08:32,374
You're so embarrassing.

1821
01:08:32,441 --> 01:08:34,443
All you need is a good donut, Poong.

1822
01:08:34,510 --> 01:08:36,245
It looks kind of weird.

1823
01:08:36,312 --> 01:08:38,948
It's rising. That's all I needed to see.

1824
01:08:39,014 --> 01:08:40,950
Try Little Tiger's dish too.

1825
01:08:41,016 --> 01:08:42,418
What can I try?

1826
01:08:42,485 --> 01:08:46,388
-Try the carrot honey.
-Carrot honey.

1827
01:08:46,455 --> 01:08:49,258
-I've never seen it before.
-Tell us what it's like, Nam-no.

1828
01:08:49,325 --> 01:08:51,360
How exactly does carrot honey taste?

1829
01:08:51,427 --> 01:08:52,795
Will she take Poong down?

1830
01:08:52,862 --> 01:08:55,898
I think she'll catch him
with this carrot, carrot!

1831
01:08:55,965 --> 01:08:57,433
What is that?

1832
01:08:57,766 --> 01:08:59,201
UNSURE

1833
01:08:59,268 --> 01:09:01,070
-Is that so?
-He's good.

1834
01:09:01,136 --> 01:09:03,272
-The amount of salt is perfection.
-Thank you.

1835
01:09:04,173 --> 01:09:05,374
-Did she add salt?
-Yes.

1836
01:09:05,441 --> 01:09:06,442
It's sweet and salty.

1837
01:09:06,509 --> 01:09:07,776
-Three minutes left.
-That's to die for.

1838
01:09:07,843 --> 01:09:08,844
PLATING HER FIRST DISH!

1839
01:09:08,911 --> 01:09:11,847
Three minutes.
Little Tiger, your <i>tteok</i> must be ready.

1840
01:09:11,914 --> 01:09:13,015
SWEET, SALTY CARROT HONEY

1841
01:09:13,315 --> 01:09:15,484
FINISHED HEATING UP THE CARROT CREAM

1842
01:09:15,551 --> 01:09:17,119
Blend it once more when you're done.

1843
01:09:17,186 --> 01:09:20,422
-Blend it once more.
-I was going to.

1844
01:09:20,489 --> 01:09:23,592
9. ADD BUTTER TO THE CREAM
AND BLEND ONCE AGAIN

1845
01:09:25,194 --> 01:09:27,596
The more it cooks,
the less it looks like a carrot.

1846
01:09:27,663 --> 01:09:30,633
-These just look like donuts.
-I see.

1847
01:09:30,699 --> 01:09:32,201
Two minutes.

1848
01:09:32,268 --> 01:09:33,802
-The donuts are ready.
-It's hot.

1849
01:09:33,869 --> 01:09:36,172
-The donuts.
-The donuts.

1850
01:09:36,238 --> 01:09:38,073
-Wait.
-How are these carrots?

1851
01:09:38,140 --> 01:09:39,542
It looks a bit…

1852
01:09:40,009 --> 01:09:41,810
HE'S INTO THESE THINGS

1853
01:09:41,877 --> 01:09:43,979
They sort of resemble carrots.

1854
01:09:44,046 --> 01:09:47,249
-They don't look like carrots.
-It doesn't look that great.

1855
01:09:47,316 --> 01:09:49,485
-Ugly carrots.
-Yes.

1856
01:09:49,552 --> 01:09:51,520
Those look good.

1857
01:09:52,254 --> 01:09:53,789
It looks like Chef Si-hyeon

1858
01:09:53,856 --> 01:09:56,992
-is adding cilantro to the carrot pickles.
-I see.

1859
01:09:57,660 --> 01:09:59,929
I added some before,
but it didn't smell strong enough.

1860
01:09:59,995 --> 01:10:02,731
-We don't know how the <i>tteok</i> will look.
-One minute and 30 seconds.

1861
01:10:02,798 --> 01:10:03,966
It's going fine.

1862
01:10:04,033 --> 01:10:07,636
-She's calm for a first-timer.
-She's so calm. She's doing good.

1863
01:10:07,703 --> 01:10:09,071
CARROT HONEY, CARROT PICKLES

1864
01:10:09,138 --> 01:10:12,675
How will the <i>tteok</i> and donuts turn out?

1865
01:10:12,741 --> 01:10:16,111
How the <i>tteok</i> and the donuts turn out
will be the most important.

1866
01:10:16,178 --> 01:10:17,446
He fishes them out.

1867
01:10:17,513 --> 01:10:19,481
-Are those carrots?
-Carrots.

1868
01:10:19,548 --> 01:10:21,884
Gosh, that's supposed to be a carrot?

1869
01:10:21,951 --> 01:10:23,953
-Like carrots covered in dirt.
-Carrots still in dirt.

1870
01:10:24,019 --> 01:10:25,921
You have less than a minute.

1871
01:10:26,155 --> 01:10:27,189
STAYING CALM

1872
01:10:27,256 --> 01:10:29,024
-<i>Tteok</i>.
-It's like a carrot with dirt on it.

1873
01:10:29,091 --> 01:10:30,993
-You need that <i>tteok</i>, Si-hyeon!
-Okay!

1874
01:10:31,060 --> 01:10:32,161
What are you eating, Nam-no?

1875
01:10:32,228 --> 01:10:35,164
-A carrot.
-Why are you eating a carrot?

1876
01:10:35,231 --> 01:10:37,600
-Forty seconds.
-You need to plate them now.

1877
01:10:37,666 --> 01:10:39,602
-Forty seconds.
-No time to do anything more.

1878
01:10:39,668 --> 01:10:40,703
CALM UNTIL THE END

1879
01:10:40,769 --> 01:10:42,238
Thirty-five seconds.

1880
01:10:42,304 --> 01:10:43,906
-Oh, no!
-Slow down. You have some time.

1881
01:10:44,273 --> 01:10:45,975
LASTLY, CARROT SEOLGI!

1882
01:10:47,009 --> 01:10:49,578
POONG PICKS UP CILANTRO

1883
01:10:50,379 --> 01:10:51,780
NO WAY

1884
01:10:51,847 --> 01:10:52,848
HE PUTS THE WHOLE THING IN?

1885
01:10:52,915 --> 01:10:55,351
-It's a carrot.
-He's putting it in.

1886
01:10:55,417 --> 01:10:57,987
-It looks like a carrot!
-It's too hot!

1887
01:10:58,053 --> 01:11:00,556
-I didn't expect him to do that!
-It's hot!

1888
01:11:01,257 --> 01:11:03,158
-Is that cilantro?
-I didn't expect him to do that!

1889
01:11:03,225 --> 01:11:04,660
It's hot!

1890
01:11:05,094 --> 01:11:06,695
FINISHES HER THREE CARROT DISHES

1891
01:11:07,263 --> 01:11:08,897
SI-HYEON FINISHES CAME TO CARROT POONG

1892
01:11:08,964 --> 01:11:10,366
Little Tiger finishes.

1893
01:11:10,432 --> 01:11:12,735
-Make a hole with a chopstick!
-Is that cilantro?

1894
01:11:12,801 --> 01:11:14,603
-Poong's carrot!
-Good.

1895
01:11:14,670 --> 01:11:18,073
Carrot-shaped donut. It looks like one!

1896
01:11:18,140 --> 01:11:21,343
IT TURNED INTO A CARROT!

1897
01:11:22,911 --> 01:11:24,146
It looks like a real carrot.

1898
01:11:24,713 --> 01:11:26,148
It looks like a carrot!

1899
01:11:27,416 --> 01:11:30,753
FLIPPING ITS MESSY HAIR

1900
01:11:30,819 --> 01:11:33,389
-Ten. Nine. Eight.
-You did it!

1901
01:11:33,455 --> 01:11:36,525
-Seven.
-Seven. He's done. Poong is done too.

1902
01:11:38,694 --> 01:11:40,396
Wait, what? That's a real carrot.

1903
01:11:41,030 --> 01:11:43,599
It turned into a carrot
as soon as he put cilantro in.

1904
01:11:43,666 --> 01:11:45,034
MADE A FAKE CARROT WITH A REAL CARROT

1905
01:11:45,934 --> 01:11:48,003
And he had time to spare.

1906
01:11:48,070 --> 01:11:49,938
This <i>tteok</i> looks good too.

1907
01:11:50,005 --> 01:11:52,041
He has great ideas as a webtoon artist.

1908
01:11:52,608 --> 01:11:53,642
Great job.

1909
01:11:54,543 --> 01:11:56,512
-Goodness.
-I'm glad I finished.

1910
01:11:56,578 --> 01:12:01,684
Both dishes for Carrot Heaven
have been made for Jin-young.

1911
01:12:01,750 --> 01:12:03,585
AMAZED

1912
01:12:03,652 --> 01:12:05,821
I didn't think he could make a carrot,

1913
01:12:05,888 --> 01:12:10,092
but it turned into one
as soon as he put the stem inside.

1914
01:12:10,159 --> 01:12:13,796
Little Tiger, any thoughts
after your 15-minute cook-off?

1915
01:12:13,862 --> 01:12:15,531
I feel like I just woke up.

1916
01:12:15,597 --> 01:12:17,700
-I don't remember anything.
-You just woke up?

1917
01:12:17,766 --> 01:12:19,401
-No memories?
-She blacked out.

1918
01:12:19,468 --> 01:12:24,506
You remembered Sung-jun's tip,
that you should finish before Poong,

1919
01:12:24,573 --> 01:12:26,508
-and rang the bell first.
-Excellent job.

1920
01:12:26,575 --> 01:12:30,245
Please try Chef Si-hyeon's dish first.

1921
01:12:30,713 --> 01:12:33,349
3 CARROT DISHES
CARROT PICKLES, CARROT HONEY,

1922
01:12:33,415 --> 01:12:35,417
AND CARROT SEOLGI

1923
01:12:35,918 --> 01:12:38,654
RAWR! CAPTURED CARROT FLAVOR
WITH DRIED CARROT SLICES

1924
01:12:39,254 --> 01:12:42,624
CHEF KIM SI-HYEON'S CAME TO CARROT POONG

1925
01:12:42,691 --> 01:12:44,159
-She did a good job.
-Yes.

1926
01:12:44,226 --> 01:12:46,028
-It's carrot <i>seolgi.</i>
-Actually,

1927
01:12:46,095 --> 01:12:49,932
the steamer overflowed a bit,
which made the lower part mushy.

1928
01:12:49,998 --> 01:12:52,101
But the top is drier,

1929
01:12:52,167 --> 01:12:54,002
so the balance should be okay.

1930
01:12:54,069 --> 01:12:56,338
-The middle ground.
-Please try just the <i>tteok</i>,

1931
01:12:56,405 --> 01:12:59,441
then with some carrot honey.

1932
01:12:59,508 --> 01:13:01,810
When you need to refresh your mouth,

1933
01:13:01,877 --> 01:13:03,912
you can have some pickles.

1934
01:13:04,413 --> 01:13:05,781
FIRST, JUST THE CARROT SEOLGI

1935
01:13:05,848 --> 01:13:07,149
This is her first dish.

1936
01:13:10,185 --> 01:13:12,788
She made <i>seolgi</i>, steamed rice cake,

1937
01:13:12,855 --> 01:13:16,358
with dried carrot slices in the middle.

1938
01:13:16,425 --> 01:13:17,426
What's it like?

1939
01:13:18,160 --> 01:13:21,163
As she mentioned, the bottom

1940
01:13:21,230 --> 01:13:23,799
is a little wet, but the top is dry.

1941
01:13:23,866 --> 01:13:25,934
So everything comes together.

1942
01:13:26,001 --> 01:13:28,003
-It's just as she said.
-It meets in the middle.

1943
01:13:28,070 --> 01:13:31,907
The texture of <i>tteok</i> and this sweet carrot

1944
01:13:31,974 --> 01:13:33,842
create a nice harmony.

1945
01:13:33,909 --> 01:13:36,044
She must've done it intentionally.

1946
01:13:36,111 --> 01:13:38,747
You can try some with carrot honey.

1947
01:13:38,814 --> 01:13:41,083
I wanted you to experience
that raw carrot aroma,

1948
01:13:41,150 --> 01:13:42,751
-so I made it raw.
-The raw carrot aroma.

1949
01:13:42,818 --> 01:13:44,920
He said he liked carrots.

1950
01:13:44,987 --> 01:13:46,922
Does it help you enjoy
the raw carrot aroma?

1951
01:13:46,989 --> 01:13:48,090
CURIOUS

1952
01:13:48,791 --> 01:13:50,058
MMM

1953
01:13:50,125 --> 01:13:52,628
The slices in the middle of the <i>tteok</i>

1954
01:13:52,694 --> 01:13:56,698
has the sweetness of pumpkin porridge.

1955
01:13:56,765 --> 01:13:58,133
But with a touch of honey,

1956
01:13:58,200 --> 01:14:01,904
it turns into the kind of sweetness
that the younger generation likes.

1957
01:14:01,970 --> 01:14:06,375
This one has a lighter kind of sweetness,
as opposed to something with weight.

1958
01:14:06,442 --> 01:14:08,110
The combo is delightful.

1959
01:14:08,911 --> 01:14:10,712
The harmony of old and new sweet.

1960
01:14:10,779 --> 01:14:12,781
Now, the pickles.

1961
01:14:12,848 --> 01:14:14,483
WHAT ABOUT THE PALATE CLEANSER?

1962
01:14:15,150 --> 01:14:16,285
Carrot pickles.

1963
01:14:17,019 --> 01:14:19,588
NODS APPROVINGLY

1964
01:14:19,655 --> 01:14:22,491
I love French carrot salad,

1965
01:14:22,558 --> 01:14:24,860
and I would love to make this at home.

1966
01:14:24,927 --> 01:14:28,297
I'm really into the sourness of vinegar,

1967
01:14:28,363 --> 01:14:30,632
so I pour in a lot
even when I eat <i>naengmyeon</i>.

1968
01:14:30,699 --> 01:14:35,404
I made pickling juice with vinegar,
sugar, salt, water, and cilantro stems.

1969
01:14:35,971 --> 01:14:37,473
And it's really good.

1970
01:14:37,539 --> 01:14:39,007
Sweet and sour.

1971
01:14:39,074 --> 01:14:40,709
CLEARED

1972
01:14:40,776 --> 01:14:43,145
She made all three dishes
that she said she would,

1973
01:14:43,212 --> 01:14:46,815
including carrot <i>seolgi</i>, carrot honey,

1974
01:14:46,882 --> 01:14:48,183
and carrot pickles.

1975
01:14:48,250 --> 01:14:50,118
I didn't think she'd finish everything,
but she did.

1976
01:14:50,185 --> 01:14:53,055
-She did.
-She made all three of them.

1977
01:14:53,121 --> 01:14:55,724
When you get tired of eating this,
you can go to this,

1978
01:14:55,791 --> 01:14:57,259
and continue the cycle.

1979
01:14:57,559 --> 01:14:58,694
RELIEVED

1980
01:14:58,760 --> 01:15:00,062
-It's delicious.
-All right.

1981
01:15:00,128 --> 01:15:01,129
A THUMBS-UP

1982
01:15:01,196 --> 01:15:04,266
-And next?
-Next, Poong Deok-juk.

1983
01:15:04,333 --> 01:15:06,268
<i>I'll Make Carrot With Carrot.</i>

1984
01:15:06,335 --> 01:15:10,572
CARROT MADE WITH CARROT BY POONG'S MAGIC

1985
01:15:11,139 --> 01:15:15,077
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
I'LL MAKE CARROT WITH CARROT

1986
01:15:15,577 --> 01:15:17,713
ABOUT TO SERVE POONG'S DISH

1987
01:15:17,779 --> 01:15:20,015
-Poong Deok-juk.
-How should he eat it?

1988
01:15:20,082 --> 01:15:22,484
Should he begin with the greens?

1989
01:15:22,951 --> 01:15:24,486
CAN'T HELP BUT FACEPALM

1990
01:15:24,553 --> 01:15:26,788
-He's an artist.
-This is unbelievable.

1991
01:15:26,855 --> 01:15:28,524
He'll chuckle as soon as he has a bite.

1992
01:15:28,590 --> 01:15:30,526
Do you like the carrot shape?

1993
01:15:30,959 --> 01:15:32,828
JUST LOOKING AT IT MAKES HIM LAUGH

1994
01:15:32,895 --> 01:15:34,196
I thought it was a real carrot.

1995
01:15:35,831 --> 01:15:38,100
But the greens don't look too fresh.

1996
01:15:38,800 --> 01:15:39,801
It's been a while.

1997
01:15:39,868 --> 01:15:41,136
How should he tackle this?

1998
01:15:41,203 --> 01:15:43,438
Well, just pick up the carrot,

1999
01:15:44,039 --> 01:15:46,675
have a spoon of the cream,
and then a bite of the carrot.

2000
01:15:46,742 --> 01:15:49,278
-With my hand?
-Or you can use your fork.

2001
01:15:49,344 --> 01:15:51,480
-However you like.
-That sauce was good.

2002
01:15:51,547 --> 01:15:52,548
CARROT CREAM FIRST

2003
01:15:52,614 --> 01:15:54,683
-First, the carrot cream.
-Was it good?

2004
01:15:55,183 --> 01:15:56,718
-It looks good.
-It must be chewy.

2005
01:15:56,785 --> 01:15:58,453
What about the texture? Was it cooked?

2006
01:16:00,589 --> 01:16:01,790
-It's really good.
-Is it?

2007
01:16:02,357 --> 01:16:03,692
AS HE PREDICTED

2008
01:16:03,759 --> 01:16:05,694
-It's an emergency.
-He's done it again.

2009
01:16:05,761 --> 01:16:06,795
Little Tiger, emergency.

2010
01:16:07,162 --> 01:16:09,197
TRIES IT WITH THE DONUT THIS TIME

2011
01:16:10,065 --> 01:16:11,400
Now, with the donut.

2012
01:16:12,701 --> 01:16:14,503
WITH BATED BREATH

2013
01:16:14,703 --> 01:16:16,004
KIM POONG'S MAGIC AT WORK

2014
01:16:16,071 --> 01:16:17,906
KIM POONG'S MAGIC STOPS

2015
01:16:18,574 --> 01:16:21,143
-Is it not cooked?
-Is it not so good with the donut?

2016
01:16:21,209 --> 01:16:23,412
Actually, I'm not that into donuts.

2017
01:16:23,679 --> 01:16:24,680
EXCHANGING EMOTIONS

2018
01:16:24,746 --> 01:16:27,082
-But…
-He doesn't like it, but…

2019
01:16:28,450 --> 01:16:30,118
But with this soup,

2020
01:16:30,185 --> 01:16:31,987
it doesn't taste greasy at all.

2021
01:16:32,054 --> 01:16:34,122
-Not greasy at all.
-It's an emergency, Little Tiger.

2022
01:16:34,189 --> 01:16:35,424
It's an emergency.

2023
01:16:35,490 --> 01:16:38,727
-You don't like how greasy donuts are.
-So I don't really like them.

2024
01:16:38,794 --> 01:16:43,031
But this didn't feel greasy at all
when I had it with the soup.

2025
01:16:43,098 --> 01:16:45,400
You should try it with the cilantro too.

2026
01:16:45,467 --> 01:16:47,769
Is that for decor or can he eat it?

2027
01:16:47,836 --> 01:16:50,038
Well, it was for the presentation,

2028
01:16:50,105 --> 01:16:52,407
-but if he wants…
-I do like cilantro,

2029
01:16:52,474 --> 01:16:54,176
but not this much.

2030
01:16:54,476 --> 01:16:55,811
TOO MUCH EVEN FOR THE CILANTRO FAN

2031
01:16:55,877 --> 01:16:57,412
I don't like it this much.

2032
01:16:57,479 --> 01:16:59,481
-So he doesn't have to?
-He doesn't.

2033
01:16:59,548 --> 01:17:01,216
Try it with a few leaves.

2034
01:17:01,283 --> 01:17:03,919
He'll try some with cilantro,
although it has wilted.

2035
01:17:03,986 --> 01:17:05,787
It's probably better if you don't eat it.

2036
01:17:06,488 --> 01:17:07,589
Why is he trying that?

2037
01:17:07,656 --> 01:17:09,558
-He likes cilantro, so…
-Okay.

2038
01:17:09,625 --> 01:17:12,461
-The fridge owner tries it with the cream.
-Does it go well with carrots?

2039
01:17:13,562 --> 01:17:14,663
DO CILANTRO AND CARROT GO WELL?

2040
01:17:14,730 --> 01:17:16,331
-After all, he served it.
-Deep-fried…

2041
01:17:16,698 --> 01:17:17,733
CHEWING

2042
01:17:17,799 --> 01:17:19,067
Do they go well?

2043
01:17:19,134 --> 01:17:20,836
Very well.

2044
01:17:20,902 --> 01:17:23,171
-You got lucky.
-But why?

2045
01:17:23,238 --> 01:17:25,974
-Why do they go well?
-I wonder why.

2046
01:17:26,041 --> 01:17:27,042
He always makes you wonder.

2047
01:17:27,109 --> 01:17:29,811
He didn't want you to eat it,
but he got lucky, anyway.

2048
01:17:31,780 --> 01:17:33,582
How's the texture of the donut?

2049
01:17:33,649 --> 01:17:36,251
It's chewy,

2050
01:17:36,318 --> 01:17:40,222
but not so chewy
that it's tough to swallow.

2051
01:17:40,288 --> 01:17:42,324
It just slides down smoothly.

2052
01:17:44,493 --> 01:17:45,494
ANOTHER THUMBS-UP

2053
01:17:45,894 --> 01:17:47,496
IT'S TOUGH TO GUESS THE WINNER

2054
01:17:47,562 --> 01:17:50,098
-He always does this.
-Our gatekeeper.

2055
01:17:50,165 --> 01:17:52,034
Do you have some for Yu-jin?

2056
01:17:52,100 --> 01:17:54,069
-I'm dying to try it.
-Right?

2057
01:17:54,136 --> 01:17:58,407
Please try Little Tiger's <i>tteok</i>.

2058
01:17:58,473 --> 01:17:59,741
It looks quite good.

2059
01:18:00,742 --> 01:18:02,377
Try the carrot <i>tteok</i>,

2060
01:18:02,944 --> 01:18:05,981
-carrot pickles, and carrot honey.
-I like this.

2061
01:18:08,417 --> 01:18:09,818
It's been steamed nicely.

2062
01:18:09,885 --> 01:18:11,920
Isn't the <i>tteok</i> delicious?

2063
01:18:11,987 --> 01:18:13,422
It's so good.

2064
01:18:13,755 --> 01:18:14,756
TREMBLING IN FEAR

2065
01:18:14,823 --> 01:18:16,491
It must've turned out well.

2066
01:18:16,558 --> 01:18:19,661
I'm someone who doesn't like carrots.

2067
01:18:20,495 --> 01:18:24,599
Yet I find it so crazy
that it tastes as sweet as a pumpkin.

2068
01:18:24,666 --> 01:18:26,668
-But these are carrots.
-Exactly.

2069
01:18:26,735 --> 01:18:29,037
It has the sweetness
without the carrot flavor.

2070
01:18:29,104 --> 01:18:30,105
It's delicious.

2071
01:18:32,708 --> 01:18:35,277
When you make white rice <i>seolgi</i>,

2072
01:18:35,343 --> 01:18:37,179
<i>there's a process you call "watering,"</i>

2073
01:18:37,245 --> 01:18:40,015
<i>which is quite a sensitive process.</i>

2074
01:18:40,082 --> 01:18:43,351
The moment you add a drop more,
the <i>tteok</i> will become too chewy.

2075
01:18:43,418 --> 01:18:46,755
But she did a great job with that
despite the lack of time.

2076
01:18:46,822 --> 01:18:49,391
It may seem like an ordinary Korean dish,

2077
01:18:49,458 --> 01:18:52,527
but she served it
with pickles and carrot honey

2078
01:18:52,594 --> 01:18:54,596
to add some freshness to the experience.

2079
01:18:54,663 --> 01:18:56,331
It was an interesting interpretation.

2080
01:18:56,398 --> 01:18:59,701
-Next, Webtoon Artist Poong's dish.
-I'm dying to try this.

2081
01:18:59,768 --> 01:19:02,537
-It's Poong's dish.
-How did he…

2082
01:19:04,840 --> 01:19:07,375
KIM POONG'S MAGIC IS IN ACTION!

2083
01:19:07,776 --> 01:19:10,445
HOW DOES THIS MAKE ANY SENSE?

2084
01:19:10,512 --> 01:19:12,814
-What is this cream?
-Wow.

2085
01:19:12,881 --> 01:19:14,549
SAVORING

2086
01:19:14,616 --> 01:19:15,617
Wow.

2087
01:19:16,885 --> 01:19:18,920
AS ALWAYS, HE MAKES YOU LAUGH

2088
01:19:19,254 --> 01:19:21,356
IT'S ME, KIM POONG

2089
01:19:21,723 --> 01:19:24,025
INDULGING

2090
01:19:24,092 --> 01:19:26,561
I feel like someone woke me up
while I was dozing off.

2091
01:19:26,895 --> 01:19:28,230
AGREED

2092
01:19:28,864 --> 01:19:30,599
Why does it taste like cheese?

2093
01:19:31,166 --> 01:19:33,168
-Because I used cheese.
-You did?

2094
01:19:34,536 --> 01:19:35,804
I wondered why.

2095
01:19:35,871 --> 01:19:38,073
Cilantro goes so well with this.

2096
01:19:38,140 --> 01:19:40,575
I understand
why you reacted the way you did.

2097
01:19:41,543 --> 01:19:44,846
-Like, "Why do they go well together?"
-It's really good.

2098
01:19:44,913 --> 01:19:46,615
That was the first thought I had.

2099
01:19:46,681 --> 01:19:48,717
I personally love this donut.

2100
01:19:48,784 --> 01:19:50,118
GETS UP

2101
01:19:50,185 --> 01:19:52,587
It almost feels like eating cheese.

2102
01:19:52,654 --> 01:19:54,990
It's quite appealing.

2103
01:19:55,056 --> 01:19:56,892
The donut was appealing.

2104
01:19:56,958 --> 01:19:58,527
I can't believe this.

2105
01:19:58,593 --> 01:20:03,031
There was never a moment
when Poong had more stars than I did.

2106
01:20:03,098 --> 01:20:04,966
-But today…
-Could it happen?

2107
01:20:05,033 --> 01:20:08,603
-He'll have three stars if he wins.
-Yes, if he wins.

2108
01:20:08,670 --> 01:20:10,806
I have never had this thought,

2109
01:20:10,872 --> 01:20:16,011
but Korea may have lost
a creative genius chef

2110
01:20:16,077 --> 01:20:17,345
and got a webtoon artist instead.

2111
01:20:19,781 --> 01:20:22,651
Chef Ho-young,
you've tried the food on <i>CCW2</i>.

2112
01:20:22,717 --> 01:20:24,786
-He would've made the top three.
-The top three?

2113
01:20:24,853 --> 01:20:26,655
He would've made the top three?

2114
01:20:26,721 --> 01:20:28,890
-The donut is a little salty.
-It is.

2115
01:20:28,957 --> 01:20:32,060
So the sweetness of the sauce
adds a perfect balance.

2116
01:20:32,127 --> 01:20:33,628
-The balance.
-Yes.

2117
01:20:33,695 --> 01:20:35,063
I'm in shock.

2118
01:20:36,131 --> 01:20:38,166
It looks like it shouldn't be delicious.

2119
01:20:39,234 --> 01:20:40,235
It shouldn't be good?

2120
01:20:40,302 --> 01:20:42,637
I really want to learn
how he made that donut.

2121
01:20:43,672 --> 01:20:46,842
Little Tiger, have you tried his dish?

2122
01:20:46,908 --> 01:20:49,377
-I finally got to.
-You finally did.

2123
01:20:49,444 --> 01:20:50,846
I've been dying to try his dish.

2124
01:20:50,912 --> 01:20:53,381
I understand
why everyone reacts the way they do.

2125
01:20:53,949 --> 01:20:54,950
However,

2126
01:20:55,016 --> 01:20:56,651
it didn't taste much like carrots.

2127
01:20:56,718 --> 01:20:58,286
-Gosh.
-You picked that out.

2128
01:20:58,353 --> 01:21:00,589
After all, the theme is Carrot Heaven.

2129
01:21:00,655 --> 01:21:02,591
-That's the theme.
-It needed more carrot flavor?

2130
01:21:02,657 --> 01:21:03,658
She got me.

2131
01:21:03,725 --> 01:21:07,195
-Little Tiger is brave and determined.
-She got him.

2132
01:21:07,262 --> 01:21:08,563
She's so shrewd.

2133
01:21:08,630 --> 01:21:10,732
It's your time to choose.

2134
01:21:10,799 --> 01:21:12,534
Jin-young is deep in thought.

2135
01:21:12,601 --> 01:21:14,636
I feel like getting drunk,

2136
01:21:14,703 --> 01:21:17,239
but someone keeps slapping me
and waking me up.

2137
01:21:17,305 --> 01:21:19,241
You want to get drunk.

2138
01:21:19,307 --> 01:21:21,576
-And enjoy this a little.
-And enjoy this.

2139
01:21:21,643 --> 01:21:24,679
-But it feels like, "Get up!"
-"Get up! Or you'll freeze to death!"

2140
01:21:24,746 --> 01:21:26,748
-He just wants to be drunk.
-I'm in that state.

2141
01:21:27,215 --> 01:21:28,550
THERE'S DECISION HELL
AFTER CARROT HEAVEN

2142
01:21:28,617 --> 01:21:30,719
He says it's tough to choose,

2143
01:21:30,785 --> 01:21:32,120
but he must.

2144
01:21:32,187 --> 01:21:34,556
Will you get drunk or get sober?

2145
01:21:34,623 --> 01:21:37,025
<i>Press one for Little Tiger, Kim Si-hyeon.</i>

2146
01:21:37,092 --> 01:21:39,461
<i>Press two for Poong Deok-juk, Kim Poong.</i>

2147
01:21:39,861 --> 01:21:41,162
IN AGONY

2148
01:21:41,229 --> 01:21:43,565
Little Tiger versus Poong Deok-juk.

2149
01:21:43,632 --> 01:21:45,734
-He pressed it.
-Okay.

2150
01:21:45,800 --> 01:21:47,402
Carrot Heaven.

2151
01:21:47,469 --> 01:21:50,138
Let's find out who won!

2152
01:21:50,205 --> 01:21:51,806
-Show us!
-I want to know.

2153
01:21:51,873 --> 01:21:53,775
The theme of this round was carrots.

2154
01:21:53,842 --> 01:21:56,645
-Did Little Tiger, Kim Si-hyeon…
-She must be nervous.

2155
01:21:56,711 --> 01:21:59,481
…win her first star on her first day here?

2156
01:21:59,547 --> 01:22:03,752
Or did Webtoon Artist Kim Poong
take Little Tiger down

2157
01:22:03,818 --> 01:22:07,789
and become the joint first place
with his third star?

2158
01:22:07,856 --> 01:22:10,659
Who did Jin-young choose?

2159
01:22:10,725 --> 01:22:13,094
Which one did he like better?

2160
01:22:13,662 --> 01:22:16,665
Which carrot dish?

2161
01:22:16,731 --> 01:22:18,333
KIM POONG WINS

2162
01:22:18,700 --> 01:22:20,001
I'LL MAKE CARROT WITH CARROT WINS

2163
01:22:20,068 --> 01:22:21,536
Kim Poong wins!

2164
01:22:21,603 --> 01:22:23,571
-Arr!
-Kim Poong!

2165
01:22:23,638 --> 01:22:25,206
He's in first place!

2166
01:22:25,273 --> 01:22:27,375
This is crazy.

2167
01:22:27,876 --> 01:22:29,110
IT WAS A GREAT MATCH

2168
01:22:29,177 --> 01:22:31,212
I can't believe he won like this.

2169
01:22:31,613 --> 01:22:32,981
WHAT HAS THIS SHOW BECOME?

2170
01:22:33,048 --> 01:22:34,349
-Preposterous.
-Hyun-suk is losing?

2171
01:22:34,416 --> 01:22:35,984
The moment I had a bite of the <i>tteok</i>,

2172
01:22:36,051 --> 01:22:37,986
it was perfect for my taste.

2173
01:22:38,053 --> 01:22:41,456
But then, I had a rush of dopamine
with this one.

2174
01:22:41,523 --> 01:22:45,493
It felt like I was someone
who wanted to live in nature,

2175
01:22:45,560 --> 01:22:49,164
but this dish kept enticing me
to hang out in the city.

2176
01:22:49,230 --> 01:22:50,999
-Like neon lights?
-Yes.

2177
01:22:51,066 --> 01:22:56,237
-It must've dazzled you.
-I guess I still craved that dopamine hit.

2178
01:22:56,304 --> 01:22:57,906
Road to Kim Poong.

2179
01:22:57,973 --> 01:23:00,675
You won against the chef
who had just come from <i>CCW</i>.

2180
01:23:00,742 --> 01:23:01,743
Of course.

2181
01:23:02,844 --> 01:23:05,313
The cast of <i>CCW</i> would get
too scared to show up.

2182
01:23:05,380 --> 01:23:07,415
Poong is on a roll.

2183
01:23:07,482 --> 01:23:08,717
Why don't we hear from him?

2184
01:23:08,783 --> 01:23:11,953
First of all,
she did such a great job today,

2185
01:23:12,020 --> 01:23:13,989
so I want to give her a big hand.

2186
01:23:14,422 --> 01:23:15,423
GREAT JOB WITH THE FIRST COOK-OFF

2187
01:23:15,490 --> 01:23:16,825
It must've been nerve-racking.

2188
01:23:16,891 --> 01:23:19,160
This is <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

2189
01:23:19,227 --> 01:23:21,863
I await challenges from many chefs!

2190
01:23:22,897 --> 01:23:23,999
He's our gatekeeper.

2191
01:23:24,065 --> 01:23:25,900
He talks like a champion.

2192
01:23:25,967 --> 01:23:28,436
-But he is. He's in first place.
-He is a champion.

2193
01:23:28,503 --> 01:23:31,206
I can't believe this. In the year 2026,

2194
01:23:31,272 --> 01:23:36,211
-Poong finally surpasses Hyun-suk!
-He surpasses him!

2195
01:23:36,277 --> 01:23:38,546
Congratulations on your third star, Poong!

2196
01:23:38,947 --> 01:23:40,248
DOES THIS EVEN MAKE SENSE?

2197
01:23:40,315 --> 01:23:42,083
He surpasses Hyun-suk

2198
01:23:42,150 --> 01:23:45,353
and becomes joint first place.

2199
01:23:45,420 --> 01:23:47,522
Jong-won, Sam,

2200
01:23:47,589 --> 01:23:48,723
and Poong take the lead!

2201
01:23:48,790 --> 01:23:50,725
-It was delicious.
-Congratulations!

2202
01:23:50,792 --> 01:23:52,727
This is so wrong.

2203
01:23:52,794 --> 01:23:54,996
-This is wrong.
-Poong's era has begun.

2204
01:23:55,063 --> 01:23:58,133
-I need to start trying harder.
-He didn't even use MSG today.

2205
01:23:58,633 --> 01:24:00,568
THEY'VE COME TO CHEF & MY FRIDGE

2206
01:24:00,635 --> 01:24:02,804
CHOI MIN-JEONG AND KIM GIL-LI!

2207
01:24:02,871 --> 01:24:05,140
Appearing on our show
was on your bucket list?

2208
01:24:05,206 --> 01:24:06,608
I had continuously won medals,

2209
01:24:06,674 --> 01:24:08,276
but you never invited me.

2210
01:24:08,343 --> 01:24:10,678
-I had to win seven medals to be here.
-Seriously?

2211
01:24:10,745 --> 01:24:12,013
Just to be here?

2212
01:24:12,080 --> 01:24:13,248
She planned it for a decade.

2213
01:24:13,314 --> 01:24:14,616
She won that for our show!

2214
01:24:14,682 --> 01:24:15,850
EVERYONE IS DEEPLY MOVED

2215
01:24:15,917 --> 01:24:18,420
I was busy crying,
so it's my first time seeing this.

2216
01:24:18,486 --> 01:24:20,755
-I saw her cry.
-You saw her cry?

2217
01:24:20,822 --> 01:24:23,992
-Yet you jumped?
-Yet you jumped like that?

2218
01:24:24,059 --> 01:24:27,328
I brought back some ingredients from Italy
just in case.

2219
01:24:27,395 --> 01:24:28,830
SHE BROUGHT THEM JUST FOR THE SHOW!

2220
01:24:28,897 --> 01:24:30,498
These are our national chefs

2221
01:24:30,565 --> 01:24:33,168
who'll cook for Gil-li and Min-jeong.
Good one!

2222
01:24:33,234 --> 01:24:34,669
Moving quickly like LamborGilli.

2223
01:24:34,736 --> 01:24:36,004
Stay strong!

2224
01:24:36,071 --> 01:24:37,138
You must get closer!

2225
01:24:37,205 --> 01:24:38,206
ARGH!

2226
01:24:38,273 --> 01:24:39,874
-Poong is in a huge crisis!
-Oh, no.

2227
01:24:39,941 --> 01:24:41,242
-What is that?
-What now, Poong?

2228
01:24:41,476 --> 01:24:42,477
A DISH NO ONE CAN IMAGINE

2229
01:24:42,544 --> 01:24:44,079
Poong just tripped and fell!

2230
01:24:44,145 --> 01:24:45,480
What is that?

2231
01:24:45,547 --> 01:24:47,449
No way.

2232
01:24:48,516 --> 01:24:50,452
-It's awesome.
-She says it's awesome.

2233
01:24:50,518 --> 01:24:51,553
It's really good.

2234
01:24:51,619 --> 01:24:54,756
It was worth a decade of wait.

2235
01:24:54,823 --> 01:24:57,459
-It's good.
-I lost again?

2236
01:24:59,360 --> 01:25:01,429
Why is it so funny to see them dine?

2237
01:25:01,496 --> 01:25:03,364
How did they do this in 15 minutes?

2238
01:25:03,431 --> 01:25:04,833
-So crazy.
-This is so good.

2239
01:25:14,909 --> 01:25:19,914
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
